msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:1.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. </p><p class="division">
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:2.1"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:3.1"
msgid "Pārājikakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on expulsion (<i lang=\"pi\">pārājika</i>)"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:5.1"
msgid "Verañjakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on Verañjā"

#. </h1></div><p class="namo"><a class="sc" id="sc1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.1" href="#ms.1"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:5.2"
msgid "Namo tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sammāsambuddhassa."
msgstr "Homage to the Master, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:6.1"
msgid "The origin of the monastic law"
msgstr "The origin of the monastic law"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="sc2"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.1"></a> <a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.1.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.1.1" href="#Bu-Pj.1.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.1" href="#bd.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.1" href="#Vin.3.1"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.2" href="#ms.2"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:7.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā verañjāyaṃ viharati naḷerupucimandamūle mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi."
msgstr "At one time, the Buddha was staying at Verañjā near Naḷeru’s Nimba tree with a great Order of five hundred monks."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:7.2"
msgid "Assosi kho verañjo brāhmaṇo—"
msgstr "And a brahmin in Verañjā heard:"

#. </p><div class="sutta"><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:7.3"
msgid "“samaṇo khalu bho gotamo sakyaputto sakyakulā pabbajito verañjāyaṃ viharati naḷerupucimandamūle mahatā bhikkhusaṃghena saddhiṃ pañcamattehi bhikkhusatehi."
msgstr "“Sir, the ascetic Gotama, the Sakyan, who has gone forth from the Sakyan clan, is staying at Verañjā near Naleru’s Nimba tree with a great Order of five hundred monks."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:7.4"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ evaṃ kalyāṇo kittisaddo abbhuggato—"
msgstr "That Master Gotama has a good reputation:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.2" href="#bd.1.2"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:7.5"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’,"
msgstr "‘He is indeed a Master, a perfected one, fully awakened, complete in true insight and conduct, accomplished, knower of the world, unsurpassed trainer of tamable people, teacher of gods and humans, the Awakened One, the Master."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:7.6"
msgid "so imaṃ lokaṃ sadevakaṃ samārakaṃ sabrahmakaṃ sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiṃ pajaṃ sadevamanussaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedeti,"
msgstr "With his own insight he has realized this world with its gods, its lords of death, and its supreme beings, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans, and he makes it known to others."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:7.7"
msgid "so dhammaṃ deseti ādikalyāṇaṃ majjhekalyāṇaṃ pariyosānakalyāṇaṃ sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ;"
msgstr "He proclaims a Teaching that is good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, with the right meaning and phrasing."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:7.8"
msgid "kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ pakāseti;"
msgstr "He reveals a perfectly complete and pure spiritual life.’"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:7.9"
msgid "sādhu kho pana tathārūpānaṃ arahataṃ dassanaṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr "Itʼs good to see such perfected ones.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.1.2" href="#Bu-Pj.1.1.2"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.3" href="#ms.3"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho verañjo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then that brahmin went to the Master,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.2" href="#Vin.3.2"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:8.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr "exchanged friendly greetings with him,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:8.3"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:8.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho verañjo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And he said this,"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:8.5"
msgid "“sutaṃ metaṃ, bho gotama—"
msgstr "“I had heard, good Gotama,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:8.6"
msgid "‘na samaṇo gotamo brāhmaṇe jiṇṇe vuḍḍhe mahallake addhagate vayoanuppatte abhivādeti vā paccuṭṭheti vā āsanena vā nimantetī’ti. Tayidaṃ, bho gotama, tatheva?"
msgstr "that you donʼt bow down to old brahmins, stand up for them, or offer them a seat."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:8.7"
msgid "Na hi bhavaṃ gotamo brāhmaṇe jiṇṇe vuḍḍhe mahallake addhagate vayoanuppatte abhivādeti vā paccuṭṭheti vā āsanena vā nimanteti?"
msgstr "Now Iʼve seen that this is indeed the case."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:8.8"
msgid "Tayidaṃ, bho gotama, na sampannamevā”ti."
msgstr "This is not proper."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.4" href="#ms.4"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:9.1"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ taṃ, brāhmaṇa, passāmi sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya yamahaṃ abhivādeyyaṃ vā paccuṭṭheyyaṃ vā āsanena vā nimanteyyaṃ."
msgstr "“Brahmin, in the world with its gods, its lords of death, and its supreme beings, in this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans, I donʼt see anyone to whom I should bow down, for whom I should rise up, or to whom I should offer a seat."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.3" href="#bd.1.3"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:9.2"
msgid "Yañhi, brāhmaṇa, tathāgato abhivādeyya vā paccuṭṭheyya vā āsanena vā nimanteyya, muddhāpi tassa vipateyyā”ti."
msgstr "If the Buddha bowed down to anyone, rose up for him, or offered him a seat, his head would explode.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.1.3" href="#Bu-Pj.1.1.3"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.5" href="#ms.5"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:10.1"
msgid "“Arasarūpo bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?"
msgstr "“Good Gotama lacks taste.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:10.2"
msgid "“Atthi khvesa, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘arasarūpo samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "“There is a way one could rightly say about me that the ascetic Gotama lacks taste."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:10.3"
msgid "Ye te, brāhmaṇa, rūparasā saddarasā gandharasā rasarasā phoṭṭhabbarasā, te tathāgatassa pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṃkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr "For the taste for forms, sounds, smells, flavors, and material objects has been abandoned by the Buddha, cut off at the root, made like a palm-stump, so utterly done away with that it is incapable of reappearing."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:10.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘arasarūpo samaṇo gotamo’ti, no ca kho yaṃ tvaṃ sandhāya vadesī”ti."
msgstr "But thatʼs not what you meant.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.6" href="#ms.6"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:11.1"
msgid "“Nibbhogo bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?"
msgstr "“Good Gotama is unlikeable.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:11.2"
msgid "“Atthi khvesa, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘nibbhogo samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "“There is a way one could rightly say about me that I am unlikeable."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:11.3"
msgid "Ye te, brāhmaṇa, rūpabhogā saddabhogā gandhabhogā rasabhogā phoṭṭhabbabhogā, te tathāgatassa pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṃkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr "For the liking of forms, sounds, smells, flavors, and material objects has been abandoned by the Buddha, cut off at the root, made like a palm-stump, so utterly done away with that it is incapable of reappearing."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.4" href="#bd.1.4"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:11.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘nibbhogo samaṇo gotamo’ti, no ca kho yaṃ tvaṃ sandhāya vadesī”ti."
msgstr "But thatʼs not what you meant.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc7"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.7" href="#ms.7"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:12.1"
msgid "“Akiriyavādo bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?"
msgstr "“Good Gotama teaches non-action.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:12.2"
msgid "“Atthi khvesa, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘akiriyavādo samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "“There is a way one could rightly say about me that the ascetic Gotama teaches non-action."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:12.3"
msgid "Ahañhi, brāhmaṇa, akiriyaṃ vadāmi kāyaduccaritassa vacīduccaritassa manoduccaritassa."
msgstr "For I teach the non-doing of misconduct by body, speech, and mind;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:12.4"
msgid "Anekavihitānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ akiriyaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "I teach the non-doing of various sorts of bad, unwholesome actions."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:12.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘akiriyavādo samaṇo gotamo’ti, no ca kho yaṃ tvaṃ sandhāya vadesī”ti."
msgstr "But thatʼs not what you meant.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc8"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.8" href="#ms.8"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:13.1"
msgid "“Ucchedavādo bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?"
msgstr "“Good Gotama teaches annihilation.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:13.2"
msgid "“Atthi khvesa, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘ucchedavādo samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "“There is a way one could rightly say about me that the ascetic Gotama teaches annihilation."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:13.3"
msgid "Ahañhi, brāhmaṇa, ucchedaṃ vadāmi rāgassa dosassa mohassa."
msgstr "For I speak of the annihilation of sense desire, anger, and confusion;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:13.4"
msgid "Anekavihitānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ucchedaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr "I speak of the annihilation of various sorts of bad, unwholesome qualities."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.3" href="#Vin.3.3"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:13.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘ucchedavādo samaṇo gotamo’ti, no ca kho yaṃ tvaṃ sandhāya vadesī”ti."
msgstr "But thatʼs not what you meant.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc9"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.9" href="#ms.9"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:14.1"
msgid "“Jegucchī bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?"
msgstr "“Good Gotama is one who detests.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:14.2"
msgid "“Atthi khvesa, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘jegucchī samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "“There is a way one could rightly say about me that I detest."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.5" href="#bd.1.5"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:14.3"
msgid "Ahañhi, brāhmaṇa, jigucchāmi kāyaduccaritena vacīduccaritena manoduccaritena."
msgstr "For I detest misconduct by body, speech, and mind;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:14.4"
msgid "Anekavihitānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ samāpattiyā jigucchāmi."
msgstr "I detest being possessed of various sorts of bad, unwholesome qualities."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:14.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘jegucchī samaṇo gotamo’ti, no ca kho yaṃ tvaṃ sandhāya vadesī”ti."
msgstr "But thatʼs not what you meant.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.10" href="#ms.10"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:15.1"
msgid "“Venayiko bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?"
msgstr "“Good Gotama is an eradicator.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:15.2"
msgid "“Atthi khvesa, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘venayiko samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "“There is a way one could rightly say about me that I am an eradicator."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:15.3"
msgid "Ahañhi, brāhmaṇa, vinayāya dhammaṃ desemi rāgassa dosassa mohassa."
msgstr "For I teach for the sake of eradication of sense desire, anger, and confusion,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:15.4"
msgid "Anekavihitānaṃ pāpakānaṃ akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ vinayāya dhammaṃ desemi."
msgstr "for the eradication of various sorts bad, unwholesome qualities."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:15.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘venayiko samaṇo gotamo’ti, no ca kho yaṃ tvaṃ sandhāya vadesī”ti."
msgstr "But thatʼs not what you meant.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.11" href="#ms.11"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:16.1"
msgid "“Tapassī bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?"
msgstr "“Good Gotama is austere.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:16.2"
msgid "“Atthi khvesa, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘tapassī samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "“There is a way one could rightly say about me that I am austere."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:16.3"
msgid "Tapanīyāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pāpake akusale dhamme vadāmi, kāyaduccaritaṃ vacīduccaritaṃ manoduccaritaṃ."
msgstr "For I say that bad, unwholesome qualities—misconduct by body, speech, and mind—are to be disciplined."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:16.4"
msgid "Yassa kho, brāhmaṇa, tapanīyā pāpakā akusalā dhammā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṃkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā tamahaṃ tapassīti vadāmi."
msgstr "He who has abandoned the bad, unwholesome qualities that are to be disciplined, who has cut them off at the root, made them like a palm-stump, done away with them so utterly that they are incapable of reappearing—him I call one who is austere."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.6" href="#bd.1.6"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:16.5"
msgid "Tathāgatassa kho, brāhmaṇa, tapanīyā pāpakā akusalā dhammā pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṃkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr "Now the Buddha has abandoned the bad, unwholesome qualities that are to be disciplined, has cut them off at the root, made them like a palm tree, done away with them so utterly that they are incapable of reappearing."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:16.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘tapassī samaṇo gotamo’ti, no ca kho yaṃ tvaṃ sandhāya vadesī”ti."
msgstr "But thatʼs not what you meant."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.12" href="#ms.12"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:17.1"
msgid "“Apagabbho bhavaṃ gotamo”ti?"
msgstr "“Good Gotama is withdrawn.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:17.2"
msgid "“Atthi khvesa, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘apagabbho samaṇo gotamo’ti."
msgstr "“There is a way one could rightly say about me that I am withdrawn."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:17.3"
msgid "Yassa kho, brāhmaṇa, āyatiṃ gabbhaseyyā punabbhavābhinibbatti pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṃkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā tamahaṃ apagabbhoti vadāmi."
msgstr "For he whose future conception in a womb, whose rebirth in a future life, is abandoned and cut off at the root, made like a palm-stump, so utterly done away with that he is incapable of reappearing—him I call one who is withdrawn."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:17.4"
msgid "Tathāgatassa kho, brāhmaṇa, āyatiṃ gabbhaseyyā punabbhavābhinibbatti pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṃkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā."
msgstr "Now the Buddha’s future conception in a womb, his rebirth in a future life, is abandoned and cut off at the root, made like a palm-stump, so utterly done away with that he is incapable of reappearing."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:17.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, brāhmaṇa, pariyāyo yena maṃ pariyāyena sammā vadamāno vadeyya—‘apagabbho samaṇo gotamo’ti, no ca kho yaṃ tvaṃ sandhāya vadesi."
msgstr "But thatʼs not what you meant."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc13"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.1.4" href="#Bu-Pj.1.1.4"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.13" href="#ms.13"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:18.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, brāhmaṇa, kukkuṭiyā aṇḍāni aṭṭha vā dasa vā dvādasa vā."
msgstr "Brahmin, suppose there were a hen with eight or ten or twelve eggs,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:18.2"
msgid "Tānassu kukkuṭiyā sammā adhisayitāni sammā pariseditāni sammā paribhāvitāni."
msgstr "which she had properly covered, properly warmed, and properly incubated."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:18.3"
msgid "Yo nu kho tesaṃ kukkuṭacchāpakānaṃ paṭhamataraṃ pādanakhasikhāya vā mukhatuṇḍakena vā aṇḍakosaṃ padāletvā sotthinā abhinibbhijjeyya, kinti svāssa vacanīyo—‘jeṭṭho vā kaniṭṭho vā’”ti?"
msgstr "Is the first chick that hatches safely—after piercing through the egg-shell with its claw or its beak—to be called the eldest or the youngest?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:18.4"
msgid "“Jeṭṭhotissa, bho gotama, vacanīyo."
msgstr "“Heʼs to be called the eldest,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:18.5"
msgid "So hi nesaṃ jeṭṭho hotī”ti."
msgstr "for heʼs the eldest of those.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.4" href="#Vin.3.4"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.7" href="#bd.1.7"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:18.6"
msgid "“Evameva kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, avijjāgatāya pajāya aṇḍabhūtāya pariyonaddhāya avijjaṇḍakosaṃ padāletvā ekova loke anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho."
msgstr "“Just so, in this population without understanding, enveloped like an egg, I alone in the world have split the eggshell of ignorance and reached the unsurpassed full awakening."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:18.7"
msgid "Svāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, jeṭṭho seṭṭho lokassa."
msgstr "I, brahmin, am the world’s eldest and best."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc14"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.1.5" href="#Bu-Pj.1.1.5"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.14" href="#ms.14"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:19.1"
msgid "Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, brāhmaṇa, vīriyaṃ ahosi asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, passaddho kāyo asāraddho, samāhitaṃ cittaṃ ekaggaṃ."
msgstr "I was firmly energetic and had clarity of mindfulness; my body was tranquil and my mind unified."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:19.2"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, brāhmaṇa, vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr "Fully secluded from the five senses, secluded from unwholesome mental qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, which consists of rapture and happiness born of seclusion and is accompanied by movement of the mind."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:19.3"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā ajjhattaṃ sampasādanaṃ cetaso ekodibhāvaṃ avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhijaṃ pītisukhaṃ dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr "Through the stilling of the movement of the mind, I entered and remained in the second absorption, which has internal confidence and unification of mind and consists of rapture and happiness born of stillness."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:19.4"
msgid "Pītiyā ca virāgā upekkhako ca vihāsiṃ sato ca sampajāno, sukhañca kāyena paṭisaṃvedesiṃ, yaṃ taṃ ariyā ācikkhanti—"
msgstr "Through the fading away of rapture, I remained even-minded, mindful, and clearly comprehending, experiencing happiness directly, and I entered and remained in the third absorption of which the noble ones declare:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:19.5"
msgid "‘upekkhako satimā sukhavihārī’ti tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr "‘One is even-minded, mindful, and abides in happiness.’"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:19.6"
msgid "Sukhassa ca pahānā dukkhassa ca pahānā pubbeva somanassadomanassānaṃ atthaṅgamā adukkhamasukhaṃ upekkhāsatipārisuddhiṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ."
msgstr "Through the abandoning of happiness and suffering and the earlier ending of joy and aversion, I entered and remained in the fourth absorption, which has neither suffering nor happiness and consists of purity of mindfulness and even-mindedness."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc15"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.1.6" href="#Bu-Pj.1.1.6"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.15" href="#ms.15"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.8" href="#bd.1.8"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.1"
msgid "So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr "Then, with my mind collected, purified, cleansed, flawless, free from defilements, soft, wieldy, steady, and imperturbable, I directed it to the knowledge which is the recollection of former lives."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.2"
msgid "So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "I recollected many past lives,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.3"
msgid "ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi jātiyo cattālīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi, jātisahassampi jātisatasahassampi, anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe—"
msgstr "that is, one birth, two births, three births, four births, five births, ten births, twenty births, thirty births, forty births, fifty births, a hundred births, a thousand births, a hundred thousand births, and many eons of world dissolution, many eons of world evolution, and many eons of both dissolution and evolution, and I knew:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.4"
msgid "‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṃgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto;"
msgstr "ʻThere I had such a name, such a family, such appearance, such food, such experience of happiness and suffering, and such a life-span."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.5"
msgid "so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ;"
msgstr "Passing away from there,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.6"
msgid "tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṃgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhappaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto;"
msgstr "I was reborn elsewhere, and there I had such a name, such a family, such appearance, such food, such experience of happiness and suffering, and such a life-span."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.7"
msgid "so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti."
msgstr "Passing away from there, I was reborn here.ʼ"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.8"
msgid "Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi."
msgstr "In this way I recollected many past lives with their characteristics and particulars."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, brāhmaṇa, rattiyā paṭhame yāme paṭhamā vijjā adhigatā,"
msgstr "This was the first true insight attained by me in the first watch of the night."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.10"
msgid "avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā, tamo vihato, āloko uppanno—"
msgstr "Ignorance was dispelled and understanding arose, darkness was dispelled and light arose,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.11"
msgid "yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr "as happens to one who remains heedful, energetic, and diligent."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.9" href="#bd.1.9"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:20.12"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, brāhmaṇa, paṭhamābhinibbhidā ahosi kukkuṭacchāpakasseva aṇḍakosamhā."
msgstr "This, brahmin, was my first breaking out, like a chick from an eggshell."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc16"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.1.7" href="#Bu-Pj.1.1.7"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.16" href="#ms.16"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.1"
msgid "So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr "Then, with my mind collected, purified, cleansed, flawless, free from defilements, soft, wieldy, steady, and imperturbable, I directed it to the knowledge of the arising and passing away of beings."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.5" href="#Vin.3.5"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.2"
msgid "So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate, yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi—"
msgstr "With the purified divine eye, which surpasses that of humans, I saw beings passing away and getting reborn, inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, gone to good destinations and to bad destinations, and I understood how beings pass on according to their actions:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.3"
msgid "‘ime vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā manoduccaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā;"
msgstr "‘These beings who engaged in misconduct by body, speech, and mind, who abused the noble ones, who held wrong view and acted accordingly,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.4"
msgid "te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā."
msgstr "at the breaking up of the body after death, have been reborn in a lower realm, a bad destination, a world of misery, hell."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.5"
msgid "Ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā ariyānaṃ anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā;"
msgstr "But these beings who engaged in good conduct of body, speech, and mind, who did not abuse the noble ones, who held right view and acted accordingly,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.6"
msgid "te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti."
msgstr "at the breaking up of the body after death, have been reborn in a good destination, a heaven world.ʼ"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.7"
msgid "Iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate, yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi."
msgstr "In this way, with the purified divine eye, which surpasses that of humans, I saw beings passing away and getting reborn, inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, gone to good destinations and to bad destinations, and I understood how beings pass on according to their actions."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.8"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, brāhmaṇa, rattiyā majjhime yāme dutiyā vijjā adhigatā,"
msgstr "This was the second true insight attained by me in the middle watch of the night."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.9"
msgid "avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā, tamo vihato, āloko uppanno—"
msgstr "Ignorance was dispelled and understanding arose, darkness was dispelled and light arose,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.10"
msgid "yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr "as happens to one who remains heedful, energetic, and diligent."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:21.11"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, brāhmaṇa, dutiyābhinibbhidā ahosi kukkuṭacchāpakasseva aṇḍakosamhā."
msgstr "This, brahmin, was my second breaking out, like a chick from an eggshell."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc17"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.1.8" href="#Bu-Pj.1.1.8"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.17" href="#ms.17"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.10" href="#bd.1.10"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.1"
msgid "So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ."
msgstr "Then, with my mind collected, purified, cleansed, flawless, free from defilements, soft, wieldy, steady, and imperturbable, I directed it to the knowledge of the ending of the corruptions."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.2"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ;"
msgstr "I knew according to reality: ʻThis is suffering;ʼ ʻThis is the origin of suffering;ʼ ʻThis is the end of suffering;ʼ ʻThis is the path leading to the end of suffering.ʼ"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.3"
msgid "‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodho’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr "I knew according to reality: ʻThese are the corruptions;ʼ ʻThis is the origin of the corruptions;ʼ ʻThis is the end of the corruptions;ʼ ʻThis is the path leading to the end of the corruptions.ʼ"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.4"
msgid "Tassa me evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha."
msgstr "When I knew and saw this, my mind was freed from the corruption of sense desire, from the corruption of existence, from the corruption of views, and from the corruption of ignorance."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.5"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "When it was freed, I knew it was freed,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.6"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr "and I understood that birth had come to an end, the spiritual life had been lived, the job had been done, there was no further state of existence."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, brāhmaṇa, rattiyā pacchime yāme tatiyā vijjā adhigatā,"
msgstr "This was the third true insight attained by me in the third watch of the night."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.8"
msgid "avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā, tamo vihato, āloko uppanno—"
msgstr "Ignorance was dispelled and understanding arose, darkness was dispelled and light arose,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.9"
msgid "yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato."
msgstr "as happens to one who remains heedful, energetic, and diligent."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.6" href="#Vin.3.6"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:22.10"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, brāhmaṇa, tatiyābhinibbhidā ahosi—kukkuṭacchāpakasseva aṇḍakosamhā”ti."
msgstr "This, brahmin, was my third breaking out, like a chick from an eggshell."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc18"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.1.9" href="#Bu-Pj.1.1.9"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.18" href="#ms.18"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, verañjo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "That brahmin then said to the Master,"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.2"
msgid "“jeṭṭho bhavaṃ gotamo, seṭṭho bhavaṃ gotamo."
msgstr "“Good Gotama is the eldest; good Gotama is the best!"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.3"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "Wonderful, good Gotama, wonderful!"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya—‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;"
msgstr "Just as one might set upright what had been overturned, or reveal what had been hidden, or show the way to one who was lost, or bring a lamp into the darkness so that one with eyes might see what is there—"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.11" href="#bd.1.11"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr "just so have you made the Teaching clear in many ways."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.6"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṃghañca."
msgstr "Good Gotama, I go for refuge to you, and to the Teaching and to the Order of monks."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.7"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gataṃ."
msgstr "Please accept me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.8"
msgid "Adhivāsetu ca me bhavaṃ gotamo verañjāyaṃ vassāvāsaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr "And please consent to spend the rains at Verañjā together with the Order of monks.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.9"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Master consented by keeping silent, and the brahmin understood."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:23.10"
msgid "Atha kho verañjo brāhmaṇo bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "He then rose from his seat, bowed down to the Master, circumambulated him with his right side towards him, and departed."

#. </p></div><hr><p><a class="sc" id="sc19"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.1.2"></a> <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.2.1" href="#Bu-Pj.1.2.1"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.19" href="#ms.19"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:24.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena verañjā dubbhikkhā hoti dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā"
msgstr "At that time Verañjā was short of food and afflicted with hunger, with crops blighted and turned to straw."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:24.2"
msgid "na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr "It was not easy to get by on almsfood."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.12" href="#bd.1.12"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:24.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena uttarāpathakā assavāṇijā pañcamattehi assasatehi verañjaṃ vassāvāsaṃ upagatā honti."
msgstr "Just then some horse-dealers from Uttarāpatha entered the rainy season residence at Verañjā with five hundred horses."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:24.4"
msgid "Tehi assamaṇḍalikāsu bhikkhūnaṃ patthapatthapulakaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In the horse-pen they prepared many portions of steamed grain for the monks."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:24.5"
msgid "Bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya verañjaṃ piṇḍāya pavisitvā"
msgstr "After dressing in the morning, the monks took their bowls and robes and entered Verañjā for alms."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:24.6"
msgid "piṇḍaṃ alabhamānā assamaṇḍalikāsu piṇḍāya caritvā"
msgstr "Being unable to obtain anything, they went to the horse-pen."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:24.7"
msgid "patthapatthapulakaṃ ārāmaṃ āharitvā udukkhale koṭṭetvā koṭṭetvā paribhuñjanti."
msgstr "They then brought the portions of steamed grain back to the monastery, pounded them, and ate them."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:24.8"
msgid "Āyasmā panānando patthapulakaṃ silāyaṃ pisitvā bhagavato upanāmeti."
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda crushed a portion of steamed grain on a stone, took it to the Master,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:24.9"
msgid "Taṃ bhagavā paribhuñjati."
msgstr "and the Master ate it."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc20"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.20" href="#ms.20"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:25.1"
msgid "Assosi kho bhagavā udukkhalasaddaṃ."
msgstr "The Master heard the sound of the mortar."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:25.2"
msgid "Jānantāpi tathāgatā pucchanti, jānantāpi na pucchanti;"
msgstr "Buddhas sometimes ask knowing, and knowing sometimes do not ask;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:25.3"
msgid "kālaṃ viditvā pucchanti, kālaṃ viditvā na pucchanti;"
msgstr "they ask knowing the right time to ask, and they ask knowing the right time not to ask."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.13" href="#bd.1.13"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:25.4"
msgid "atthasaṃhitaṃ tathāgatā pucchanti, no anatthasaṃhitaṃ."
msgstr "Buddhas ask when it is beneficial, not when it is unbeneficial;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:25.5"
msgid "Anatthasaṃhite setughāto tathāgatānaṃ."
msgstr "in regard to what is unbeneficial, the Buddhas have destroyed the bridge."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:25.6"
msgid "Dvīhi ākārehi buddhā bhagavanto bhikkhū paṭipucchanti—"
msgstr "Buddhas question the monks for two reasons:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:25.7"
msgid "dhammaṃ vā desessāma, sāvakānaṃ vā sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmāti."
msgstr "to give a teaching or to lay down a training rule."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc21"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.21" href="#ms.21"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:26.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi—"
msgstr "And so the Master said to Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:26.2"
msgid "“kiṃ nu kho so, ānanda, udukkhalasaddo”ti?"
msgstr "“Ānanda, what is this sound of a mortar?”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:26.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "Ānanda informed the Master."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.7" href="#Vin.3.7"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:26.4"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, ānanda."
msgstr "“Good, good, Ānanda,"

#. <span class="note" hidden>I have supplied “the problems of famine” from the commentary (<i lang="pi">dubbhikkhe dullabhapiṇḍe imāya sallahukavuttitāya iminā ca sallekhena vijitaṃ</i>), <span class="ref">Sp.1.180.24</span>, to bring out the meaning.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:26.5"
msgid "Tumhehi, ānanda, sappurisehi vijitaṃ."
msgstr "you who are superior people have conquered the problems of famine;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:26.6"
msgid "Pacchimā janatā sālimaṃsodanaṃ atimaññissatī”ti."
msgstr "later generations will despise even rice and meat."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="sc22"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.2.2" href="#Bu-Pj.1.2.2"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.22" href="#ms.22"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He then said,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.14" href="#bd.1.14"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.4"
msgid "“etarahi, bhante, verañjā dubbhikkhā dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā."
msgstr "“At present, Venerable Sir, Verañjā is short of food and afflicted with hunger, with crops blighted and turned to straw."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.5"
msgid "Na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr "Itʼs not easy to get by almsfood."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.6"
msgid "Imissā, bhante, mahāpathaviyā heṭṭhimatalaṃ sampannaṃ—"
msgstr "Venerable Sir, the under-surface of this great earth is abounding with food,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.7"
msgid "seyyathāpi khuddamadhuṃ anīlakaṃ; evamassādaṃ."
msgstr "which tastes just like pure honey."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.8"
msgid "Sādhāhaṃ, bhante, pathaviṃ parivatteyyaṃ."
msgstr "It would be good if I could invert the earth"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.9"
msgid "Bhikkhū pappaṭakojaṃ paribhuñjissantī”ti."
msgstr "so that the monks may enjoy the nutrition in those water-plants.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.10"
msgid "“Ye pana te, moggallāna, pathavinissitā pāṇā te kathaṃ karissasī”ti?"
msgstr "“But what will you do, Moggallāna, with those creatures who are living there?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.11"
msgid "“Ekāhaṃ, bhante, pāṇiṃ abhinimminissāmi—seyyathāpi mahāpathavī."
msgstr "“Iʼll make one of my hands broad, like the great earth, and Iʼll make those creatures go there."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.12"
msgid "Ye pathavinissitā pāṇā te tattha saṅkāmessāmi."
msgstr "and Iʼll make those creatures go there."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.13"
msgid "Ekena hatthena pathaviṃ parivattessāmī”ti."
msgstr "Then with the other hand Iʼll invert the earth.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.14"
msgid "“Alaṃ, moggallāna, mā te rucci pathaviṃ parivattetuṃ."
msgstr "“Please donʼt invert the earth, Moggallāna."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.15"
msgid "Vipallāsampi sattā paṭilabheyyun”ti."
msgstr "Those creatures might lose their minds.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.16"
msgid "“Sādhu, bhante, sabbo bhikkhusaṃgho uttarakuruṃ piṇḍāya gaccheyyā”ti."
msgstr "“In that case, Venerable Sir, it would be good if the whole Order of monks could go to Uttarakuru for alms.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:27.17"
msgid "“Alaṃ, moggallāna, mā te rucci sabbassa bhikkhusaṃghassa uttarakuruṃ piṇḍāya gamanan”ti."
msgstr "“No, Moggallāna, please donʼt pursue this.”"

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="sc23"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.1.3"></a> <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.3.1" href="#Bu-Pj.1.3.1"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.23" href="#ms.23"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:28.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi—"
msgstr "At this time, while Venerable Sāriputta was in seclusion, he thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:28.2"
msgid "“katamesānaṃ kho buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosi;"
msgstr "“For which Buddhas did the dispensation not last long?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:28.3"
msgid "katamesānaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosī”ti?"
msgstr "For which Buddhas did the dispensation last long?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc24"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.24" href="#ms.24"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:29.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "In the evening, after coming out of seclusion, Sāriputta approached the Master."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:29.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "He bowed down to him, sat down to one side,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.15" href="#bd.1.15"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:29.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:29.4"
msgid "“idha mayhaṃ, bhante, rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi—"
msgstr "“Just now, Venerable Sir, while I was in seclusion, I thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:29.5"
msgid "‘katamesānaṃ kho buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosi, katamesānaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosī’ti. Katamesānaṃ nu kho, bhante, buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ brahmacariyaṃ na ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosi, katamesānaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosī”ti?"
msgstr "‘For which Buddhas did the dispensation not last long, and for which ones did it last long?’”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc25"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.25" href="#ms.25"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:30.1"
msgid "“Bhagavato ca, sāriputta, vipassissa bhagavato ca sikhissa bhagavato ca vessabhussa brahmacariyaṃ na ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosi."
msgstr "“Sāriputta, the dispensation established by Master Vipassī, Master Sikhī, and Master Vessabhū didnʼt last long."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.8" href="#Vin.3.8"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:30.2"
msgid "Bhagavato ca, sāriputta, kakusandhassa bhagavato ca koṇāgamanassa bhagavato ca kassapassa brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosī”ti."
msgstr "But the dispensation established by Master Kakusandha, Master Konāgamana, and Master Kassapa did last long.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc26"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.3.2" href="#Bu-Pj.1.3.2"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.26" href="#ms.26"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.1"
msgid "“Ko nu kho, bhante, hetu ko paccayo, yena bhagavato ca vipassissa bhagavato ca sikhissa bhagavato ca vessabhussa brahmacariyaṃ na ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosī”ti?"
msgstr "“And whatʼs the reason why the dispensation established by Master Vipassī, Master Sikhī, and Master Vessabhū didnʼt last long?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.2"
msgid "“Bhagavā ca, sāriputta, vipassī bhagavā ca sikhī bhagavā ca vessabhū kilāsuno ahesuṃ sāvakānaṃ vitthārena dhammaṃ desetuṃ."
msgstr "“Master Vipassī, Master Sikhī, and Master Vessabhū were disinclined to give detailed teachings to their disciples."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.3"
msgid "Appakañca nesaṃ ahosi suttaṃ geyyaṃ veyyākaraṇaṃ gāthā udānaṃ itivuttakaṃ jātakaṃ abbhutadhammaṃ vedallaṃ."
msgstr "They gave few discourses in prose and in prose and verse, few expositions, verses, inspired utterances, quotations, birth stories, amazing accounts, and analyses;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.4"
msgid "Apaññattaṃ sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ."
msgstr "and they didnʼt lay down training rules"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.5"
msgid "Anuddiṭṭhaṃ pātimokkhaṃ."
msgstr "or recite a monastic code."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.16" href="#bd.1.16"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.6"
msgid "Tesaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ antaradhānena buddhānubuddhānaṃ sāvakānaṃ antaradhānena ye te pacchimā sāvakā nānānāmā nānāgottā nānājaccā nānākulā pabbajitā te taṃ brahmacariyaṃ khippaññeva antaradhāpesuṃ."
msgstr "After the disappearance of those Buddhas, after the disappearance of the disciples awakened under them, those who were the last disciples—of various names, clans, and social standing, who had gone forth from various families—allowed that dispensation to disappear rapidly."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, nānāpupphāni phalake nikkhittāni suttena asaṅgahitāni tāni vāto vikirati vidhamati viddhaṃseti."
msgstr "Itʼs just like loose flowers on a flat surface: theyʼre scattered about, whirled about, and destroyed by the wind."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Whyʼs that?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.9"
msgid "Yathā taṃ suttena asaṅgahitattā."
msgstr "Because theyʼre not held together by a thread."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:31.10"
msgid "Evameva kho, sāriputta, tesaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ antaradhānena buddhānubuddhānaṃ sāvakānaṃ antaradhānena ye te pacchimā sāvakā nānānāmā nānāgottā nānājaccā nānākulā pabbajitā te taṃ brahmacariyaṃ khippaññeva antaradhāpesuṃ."
msgstr "Just so, after the disappearance of those Buddhas, after the disappearance of the disciples awakened under them, those who were the last disciples allowed that dispensation to disappear rapidly."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc27"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.27" href="#ms.27"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:32.1"
msgid "Akilāsuno ca te bhagavanto ahesuṃ sāvake cetasā ceto paricca ovadituṃ."
msgstr "But, Sāriputta, those Masters were untiring in exhorting their disciples after reading their minds."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:32.2"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, sāriputta, vessabhū bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho aññatarasmiṃ bhiṃsanake vanasaṇḍe sahassaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ cetasā ceto paricca ovadati anusāsati—"
msgstr "At one time, while staying in a certain frightening forest grove, Master Vessabhū, the Perfected and the fully Awakened One, exhorted and admonished an Order of a thousand monks, reading their minds and saying,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:32.3"
msgid "‘evaṃ vitakketha, mā evaṃ vitakkayittha;"
msgstr "‘Think like this, not like this;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:32.4"
msgid "evaṃ manasikarotha, mā evaṃ manasākattha;"
msgstr "pay attention like this, not like this;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:32.5"
msgid "idaṃ pajahatha,"
msgstr "abandon this;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:32.6"
msgid "idaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti."
msgstr "having attained this, abide in it.’"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:32.7"
msgid "Atha kho, sāriputta, tassa bhikkhusahassassa vessabhunā bhagavatā arahatā sammāsambuddhena evaṃ ovadiyamānānaṃ evaṃ anusāsiyamānānaṃ anupādāya āsavehi cittāni vimucciṃsu."
msgstr "When those thousand monks had been exhorted and admonished by Master Vessabhū, their minds were freed from the corruptions without grasping."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.17" href="#bd.1.17"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:32.8"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ, sāriputta, bhiṃsanakassa vanasaṇḍassa bhiṃsanakatasmiṃ hoti—yo koci avītarāgo taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ pavisati, yebhuyyena lomāni haṃsanti."
msgstr "But when anyone not devoid of desire entered that frightening forest grove, usually their hair would stand on end."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:32.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena bhagavato ca vipassissa bhagavato ca sikhissa bhagavato ca vessabhussa brahmacariyaṃ na ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosī”ti."
msgstr "This is the reason why the dispensation established by Master Vipassī, Master Sikhī, and Master Vessabhū did not last long.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc28"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.3.3" href="#Bu-Pj.1.3.3"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.28" href="#ms.28"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.1"
msgid "“Ko pana, bhante, hetu ko paccayo yena bhagavato ca kakusandhassa bhagavato ca koṇāgamanassa bhagavato ca kassapassa brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosī”ti?"
msgstr "“What then is the reason why the dispensation established by Master Kakusandha, Master Konāgamana, and Master Kassapa lasted long?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.9" href="#Vin.3.9"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.2"
msgid "“Bhagavā ca, sāriputta, kakusandho bhagavā ca koṇāgamano bhagavā ca kassapo akilāsuno ahesuṃ sāvakānaṃ vitthārena dhammaṃ desetuṃ."
msgstr "“Master Kakusandha, Master Konāgamana, and Master Kassapa were diligent in giving detailed teachings to their disciples."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.3"
msgid "Bahuñca nesaṃ ahosi suttaṃ geyyaṃ veyyākaraṇaṃ gāthā udānaṃ itivuttakaṃ jātakaṃ abbhutadhammaṃ vedallaṃ,"
msgstr "They gave many discourses in prose and in prose and verse, many expositions, verses, inspired utterances, quotations, birth stories, amazing accounts, and analyses;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.4"
msgid "paññattaṃ sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ,"
msgstr "and they laid down training rules"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.5"
msgid "uddiṭṭhaṃ pātimokkhaṃ."
msgstr "and recited a monastic code."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.6"
msgid "Tesaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ antaradhānena buddhānubuddhānaṃ sāvakānaṃ antaradhānena ye te pacchimā sāvakā nānānāmā nānāgottā nānājaccā nānākulā pabbajitā te taṃ brahmacariyaṃ ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ ṭhapesuṃ."
msgstr "After the disappearance of those Buddhas, after the disappearance of the disciples awakened under them, those who were the last disciples—of various names, clans, and social standing, who had gone forth from various families—made that dispensation last for a long time."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, nānāpupphāni phalake nikkhittāni suttena susaṅgahitāni, tāni vāto na vikirati na vidhamati na viddhaṃseti."
msgstr "Itʼs just like flowers on a flat surface that are held together by a thread: theyʼre not scattered about, whirled about, or destroyed by the wind."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Whyʼs that?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.9"
msgid "Yathā taṃ suttena susaṅgahitattā."
msgstr "Because theyʼre held together by a thread."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.10"
msgid "Evameva kho, sāriputta, tesaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ antaradhānena buddhānubuddhānaṃ sāvakānaṃ antaradhānena ye te pacchimā sāvakā nānānāmā nānāgottā nānājaccā nānākulā pabbajitā te taṃ brahmacariyaṃ ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ ṭhapesuṃ."
msgstr "Just so, after the disappearance of those Buddhas, after the disappearance of the disciples awakened under them, those who were the last disciples made that dispensation last for a long time."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:33.11"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, sāriputta, hetu ayaṃ paccayo yena bhagavato ca kakusandhassa bhagavato ca koṇāgamanassa bhagavato ca kassapassa brahmacariyaṃ ciraṭṭhitikaṃ ahosī”ti."
msgstr "This is the reason why the dispensation established by Master Kakusandha, Master Konāgamana, and Master Kassapa lasted long."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc29"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.3.4" href="#Bu-Pj.1.3.4"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.29" href="#ms.29"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.18" href="#bd.1.18"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:34.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto uṭṭhāyāsanā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yena bhagavā tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Then Sāriputta got up from his seat, put his robe over one shoulder, put the palms of his hands together, and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:34.2"
msgid "“etassa, bhagavā, kālo. Etassa, sugata, kālo."
msgstr "“This is the right time, Master,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:34.3"
msgid "Yaṃ bhagavā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapeyya, uddiseyya pātimokkhaṃ, yathayidaṃ brahmacariyaṃ addhaniyaṃ assa ciraṭṭhitikan”ti."
msgstr "for laying down training rules and reciting a monastic code, so that this dispensation may last for a long time.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:34.4"
msgid "“Āgamehi tvaṃ, sāriputta. Āgamehi tvaṃ, sāriputta."
msgstr "“Hold on, Sāriputta,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:34.5"
msgid "Tathāgatova tattha kālaṃ jānissati."
msgstr "the Buddha will know the right time for that."

#. <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.30" href="#ms.30-33"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.19" href="#bd.1.19"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:34.6"
msgid "Na tāva, sāriputta, satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapeti uddisati pātimokkhaṃ yāva na idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti. Yato ca kho, sāriputta, idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti, atha satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapeti uddisati pātimokkhaṃ tesaṃyeva āsavaṭṭhānīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭighātāya."
msgstr "The Teacher doesnʼt lay down training rules and recite a monastic code until the causes of corruption appear in the monastic Order."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc30"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:35.1"
msgid "Na tāva, sāriputta, idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti yāva na saṃgho rattaññumahattaṃ patto hoti."
msgstr "And they donʼt appear until the monastic Order has attained long standing,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:35.2"
msgid "Yato ca kho, sāriputta, saṃgho rattaññumahattaṃ patto hoti atha idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti, atha satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapeti uddisati pātimokkhaṃ tesaṃyeva āsavaṭṭhānīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭighātāya."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:36.1"
msgid "Na tāva, sāriputta, idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti, yāva na saṃgho vepullamahattaṃ patto hoti."
msgstr "great size,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:36.2"
msgid "Yato ca kho, sāriputta, saṃgho vepullamahattaṃ patto hoti, atha idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti, atha satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapeti uddisati pātimokkhaṃ tesaṃyeva āsavaṭṭhānīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭighātāya."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:37.1"
msgid "Na tāva, sāriputta, idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti, yāva na saṃgho lābhaggamahattaṃ patto hoti."
msgstr "an abundance of material support,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:37.2"
msgid "Yato ca kho, sāriputta, saṃgho lābhaggamahattaṃ patto hoti, atha idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti, atha satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapeti uddisati pātimokkhaṃ tesaṃyeva āsavaṭṭhānīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭighātāya."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:38.1"
msgid "Na tāva, sāriputta, idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti, yāva na saṃgho bāhusaccamahattaṃ patto hoti."
msgstr "or great learning."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.10" href="#Vin.3.10"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:38.2"
msgid "Yato ca kho, sāriputta, saṃgho bāhusaccamahattaṃ patto hoti, atha idhekacce āsavaṭṭhānīyā dhammā saṃghe pātubhavanti, atha satthā sāvakānaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapeti uddisati pātimokkhaṃ tesaṃyeva āsavaṭṭhānīyānaṃ dhammānaṃ paṭighātāya."
msgstr "When this happens, then the Teacher lays down training rules for his disciples and recites a monastic code in order to hold back those causes of corruption."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc34"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.34" href="#ms.34"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:39.1"
msgid "Nirabbudo hi, sāriputta, bhikkhusaṃgho nirādīnavo apagatakāḷako suddho sāre patiṭṭhito."
msgstr "Sāriputta, the Order of monks is devoid of immorality, devoid of danger, stainless, pure, established in the essence."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:39.2"
msgid "Imesañhi, sāriputta, pañcannaṃ bhikkhusatānaṃ yo pacchimako bhikkhu so sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo”ti."
msgstr "Even the least developed of these five hundred monks is a stream-enterer, not subject to rebirth in the lower world, fixed in destiny, bound for awakening."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="sc35"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.4" href="#Bu-Pj.1.4"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.20" href="#bd.1.20"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.35" href="#ms.35"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:40.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi—"
msgstr "Then the Master said to Ānanda,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:40.2"
msgid "“āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ, ānanda, tathāgatānaṃ yehi nimantitā vassaṃ vasanti, na te anapaloketvā janapadacārikaṃ pakkamanti."
msgstr "“Ānanda, itʼs the custom for Buddhas not to go wandering around the country without taking leave of those who invited them to spend the rains."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:40.3"
msgid "Āyāmānanda, verañjaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ apalokessāmā”ti."
msgstr "Letʼs go to the brahmin of Verañjā and take leave.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:40.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, Venerable Sir.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc36"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.36" href="#ms.36"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āyasmatā ānandena pacchāsamaṇena yena verañjassa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "The Master dressed, took his bowl and robe, and with Ānanda as his attendant, went to the dwelling of that brahmin where he sat down on the prepared seat."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.2"
msgid "Atha kho verañjo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "The brahmin approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.3"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho verañjaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ bhagavā etadavoca—"
msgstr "And the Master said,"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.11" href="#Vin.3.11"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.5"
msgid "“nimantitamha tayā, brāhmaṇa, vassaṃvuṭṭhā, apalokema taṃ,"
msgstr "“Brahmin, weʼve spent the rainy season according to your invitation, and now we take leave of you."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.6"
msgid "“icchāma mayaṃ janapadacārikaṃ pakkamitun”ti."
msgstr "We wish to depart to go wandering around the country.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.7"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bho gotama, nimantitattha mayā vassaṃvuṭṭhā;"
msgstr "“Itʼs true, good Gotama, that youʼve spent the rainy season according to my invitation,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.8"
msgid "api ca yo deyyadhammo so na dinno."
msgstr "but I havenʼt given a gift."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.9"
msgid "Tañca kho no asantaṃ,"
msgstr "Thatʼs not good."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.10"
msgid "nopi adātukamyatā, taṃ kutettha labbhā bahukiccā gharāvāsā bahukaraṇīyā."
msgstr "Itʼs not because I didnʼt want to, but because household life is busy and thereʼs much to do."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.11"
msgid "Adhivāsetu me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā”ti."
msgstr "Would you and the Order of monks please accept a meal from me tomorrow?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.12"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "The Master consented by keeping silent."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:41.13"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā verañjaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr "Then, after instructing, inspiring, and gladdening that brahmin with a teaching, the Master rose from his seat, and departed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc37"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.37" href="#ms.37"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:42.1"
msgid "Atha kho verañjo brāhmaṇo tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi—"
msgstr "The following morning the brahmin prepared various kinds of fine food in his own home and then informed the Master:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:42.2"
msgid "“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Itʼs time, good Gotama, the meal is ready.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc38"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.38" href="#ms.38"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.21" href="#bd.1.21"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:43.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena verañjassa brāhmaṇassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena."
msgstr "After dressing the following morning, the Master took his bowl and robe, and together with the Order of monks, he went to the dwelling of that brahmin and sat down on the prepared seat."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:43.2"
msgid "Atha kho verañjo brāhmaṇo buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappetvā"
msgstr "With his own hands the brahmin served various kinds of fine food to the Order of monks headed by the Buddha."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:43.3"
msgid "sampavāretvā bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ ticīvarena acchādesi, ekamekañca bhikkhuṃ ekamekena dussayugena acchādesi."
msgstr "When they were satisfied and the Master had finished his meal, the brahmin gave a set of three robes to the Master and two pieces of cloth to each monk."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:43.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā verañjaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr "The Master instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching, and then rose from his seat and departed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="sc39"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.39" href="#ms.39"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:44.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā verañjāyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā anupagamma soreyyaṃ saṅkassaṃ kaṇṇakujjaṃ yena payāgapatiṭṭhānaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "After remaining in Verañjā for as long as he liked, the Master traveled to Payāgapatiṭṭhāna via Soreyya, Saṅkassa, and Kaṇṇakujja."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:44.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā payāgapatiṭṭhāne gaṅgaṃ nadiṃ uttaritvā yena bārāṇasī tadavasari."
msgstr "There he crossed the river Ganges and continued on to Benares."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:44.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā bārāṇasiyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena vesālī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi."
msgstr "After remaining in Benares for as long as he liked, he set out wandering towards Vesālī."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:44.4"
msgid "Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena vesālī tadavasari."
msgstr "When he eventually arrived at Vesālī,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:44.5"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyanti."
msgstr "he stayed in the Great Wood, in the hall with the peaked roof."

#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="sc40"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.40" href="#ms.40"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-intro:45.1"
msgid "Verañjabhāṇavāro niṭṭhito."
msgstr "The chapter on Verañjā is finished."

#. </p><hr><h1><span class="add"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:4.1"
msgid "Pārājika 1: "
msgstr "Monks’ Expulsion 1:"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:4.2"
msgid "Paṭha­ma­pā­rāji­ka­sikkhā­pada"
msgstr "the first training rule"

#. </h1><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:5.1"
msgid "1. Sudinna­bhā­ṇavāra"
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:5.2"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.1.5"></a> <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.1" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.1"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.41" href="#ms.41"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena vesāliyā avidūre kalandagāmo nāma atthi."
msgstr "At one time Sudinna, the son of a prominent merchant,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.2"
msgid "Tattha sudinno nāma kalandaputto seṭṭhiputto hoti."
msgstr "lived in a village called Kalandaka not far from Vesālī."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.22" href="#bd.1.22"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.12" href="#Vin.3.12"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.3"
msgid "Atha kho sudinno kalandaputto sambahulehi sahāyakehi saddhiṃ vesāliṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena."
msgstr "On one occasion Sudinna went to Vesālī on some  business together with many friends."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā mahatiyā parisāya parivuto dhammaṃ desento nisinno hoti."
msgstr "Just then the Master was seated, surrounded by a great assembly of people, giving a teaching."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.5"
msgid "Addasa kho sudinno kalandaputto bhagavantaṃ mahatiyā parisāya parivutaṃ dhammaṃ desentaṃ nisinnaṃ."
msgstr "When Sudinna saw this"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.6"
msgid "Disvānassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "he thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.7"
msgid "“yannūnāhampi dhammaṃ suṇeyyan”ti."
msgstr "“Why don’t I listen to the Teaching?”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.8"
msgid "Atha kho sudinno kalandaputto yena sā parisā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He then approached that assembly"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "and sat down to one side."

#. </p><div class="sutta"><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.10"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnassa kho sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "As he was sitting there, he thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.11"
msgid "“yathā yathā kho ahaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekanta­pari­puṇṇaṃ ekanta­pari­suddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ;"
msgstr "“The way I understand the Masterʼs Teaching, itʼs not easy for one who lives in a house to lead the spiritual life perfectly complete and pure as a polished conch shell."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.12"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajeyyan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I cut off my hair and beard, put on the ocher robes, and go forth from home into homelessness?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:6.13"
msgid "Atha kho sā parisā bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr "When those people had been instructed, inspired, and gladdened by the Master, they rose from their seats, bowed down to the Master, circumambulated him with their right side towards him, and departed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.42" href="#ms.42"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho sudinno kalandaputto acira­vuṭṭhi­tāya parisāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Sudinna then approached the Master,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sudinno kalandaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "And he said to the Master:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.4"
msgid "“yathā yathāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekanta­pari­puṇṇaṃ ekanta­pari­suddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ;"
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, the way I understand the Masterʼs Teaching, itʼs not easy for one who lives in a house to lead the spiritual life perfectly complete and pure as a polished conch shell."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.5"
msgid "icchāmahaṃ, bhante, kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ."
msgstr "I want to cut off my hair and beard, put on the ocher robes, and go forth from home into homelessness."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.6"
msgid "Pabbājetu maṃ bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "Master, please give me the going forth.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.23" href="#bd.1.23"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.7"
msgid "“Anuññātosi pana tvaṃ, sudinna, mātāpitūhi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti?"
msgstr "“But, Sudinna, do you have your parents’ permission?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.8"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, bhante, anuññāto mātāpitūhi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Venerable Sir.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.9"
msgid "“Na kho, sudinna, tathāgatā ananuññātaṃ mātāpitūhi puttaṃ pabbājentī”ti."
msgstr "“Sudinna, Buddhas don’t give the going forth to the son of parents who haven’t given their permission.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:7.10"
msgid "“Sohaṃ, bhante, tathā karissāmi yathā maṃ mātāpitaro anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr "“I’ll do whatever is necessary, Venerable Sir, to get my parents’ permission.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.2" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.2"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.43" href="#ms.43"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho sudinno kalandaputto vesāliyaṃ taṃ karaṇīyaṃ tīretvā yena kalandagāmo yena mātāpitaro tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then, after finishing his business in Vesālī, Sudinna returned to Kalandaka. There he approached his parents"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā mātāpitaro etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.3"
msgid "“ammatātā, yathā yathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekanta­pari­puṇṇaṃ ekanta­pari­suddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ;"
msgstr "“Mum and dad, the way I understand the the Masterʼs Teaching, itʼs not easy for one who lives in a house to lead the spiritual life perfectly complete and pure."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.13" href="#Vin.3.13"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.4"
msgid "icchāmahaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ."
msgstr "I want to cut off my hair and beard, put on the ocher robes, and go forth from home into homelessness."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.5"
msgid "Anujānātha maṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr "Please give me permission to go forth.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa mātāpitaro sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "His parents replied,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.7"
msgid "“tvaṃ khosi, tāta sudinna, amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparihato."
msgstr "“But, Sudinna, youʼre our only child. Youʼre dear to us and we love you. You live in comfort and are well cared for;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.8"
msgid "Na tvaṃ, tāta sudinna, kiñci dukkhassa jānāsi."
msgstr "you have no experience of suffering."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.9"
msgid "Maraṇenapi mayaṃ te akāmakā vinā bhavissāma"
msgstr "Even if you died it would be against our wishes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:8.10"
msgid "kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr "So how can we allow you to go forth from home into homelessness while youʼre still living?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.44" href="#ms.44"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:9.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sudinno kalandaputto mātāpitaro etadavoca—"
msgstr "Sudinna asked his parents a second"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:9.2"
msgid "“ammatātā, yathā yathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekanta­pari­puṇṇaṃ ekanta­pari­suddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:9.3"
msgid "icchāmahaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:9.4"
msgid "Anujānātha maṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:9.5"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa mātāpitaro sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:9.6"
msgid "“tvaṃ khosi, tāta sudinna, amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparihato."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:9.7"
msgid "Na tvaṃ, tāta sudinna, kiñci dukkhassa jānāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:9.8"
msgid "Maraṇenapi mayaṃ te akāmakā vinā bhavissāma, kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:10.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho sudinno kalandaputto mātāpitaro etadavoca—"
msgstr "and a third time, but got the same reply."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:10.2"
msgid "“ammatātā, yathā yathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, nayidaṃ sukaraṃ agāraṃ ajjhāvasatā ekanta­pari­puṇṇaṃ ekanta­pari­suddhaṃ saṅkhalikhitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:10.3"
msgid "icchāmahaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajituṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:10.4"
msgid "Anujānātha maṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:10.5"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa mātāpitaro sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:10.6"
msgid "“tvaṃ khosi, tāta sudinna, amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparihato."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:10.7"
msgid "Na tvaṃ, tāta sudinna, kiñci dukkhassa jānāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:10.8"
msgid "Maraṇenapi mayaṃ te akāmakā vinā bhavissāma, kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.46" href="#ms.46"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:11.1"
msgid "Atha kho sudinno kalandaputto—“na maṃ mātāpitaro anujānanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti, tattheva anantarahitāya bhūmiyā nipajji—"
msgstr "He then lay down on the bare ground and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:11.2"
msgid "“idheva me maraṇaṃ bhavissati pabbajjā vā”ti."
msgstr "“Iʼll either die right here or go forth.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:11.3"
msgid "Atha kho sudinno kalandaputto ekampi bhattaṃ na bhuñji, dvepi bhattāni na bhuñji, tīṇipi bhattāni na bhuñji, cattāripi bhattāni na bhuñji, pañcapi bhattāni na bhuñji, chapi bhattāni na bhuñji, sattapi bhattāni na bhuñji."
msgstr "And he did not eat at the next seven meals."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.24" href="#bd.1.24"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.47" href="#ms.47"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:12.1"
msgid "Atha kho sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa mātāpitaro sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "His parents said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:12.2"
msgid "“tvaṃ khosi, tāta sudinna, amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparihato."
msgstr "“Dear Sudinna, youʼre our only child. Youʼre dear to us and we love you. You live in comfort and are well cared for;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:12.3"
msgid "Na tvaṃ, tāta sudinna, kiñci dukkhassa jānāsi."
msgstr "you have no experience of suffering."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:12.4"
msgid "Maraṇenapi mayaṃ te akāmakā vinā bhavissāma,"
msgstr "Even if you died it would be against our wishes."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:12.5"
msgid "kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya?"
msgstr "So how can we allow you to go forth from home into homelessness while youʼre still living?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:12.6"
msgid "Uṭṭhehi, tāta sudinna, bhuñja ca piva ca paricārehi ca,"
msgstr "Get up, Sudinna, eat, drink, and amuse yourself."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:12.7"
msgid "bhuñjanto pivanto paricārento kāme paribhuñjanto puññāni karonto abhiramassu."
msgstr "Enjoy sense pleasures and do acts of merit."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:12.8"
msgid "Na taṃ mayaṃ anujānāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr "We wonʼt allow you to go forth.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:12.9"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sudinno kalandaputto tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr "But Sudinna did not respond."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.48" href="#ms.48"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:13.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho …"
msgstr "His parents said the same thing a second"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:13.2"
msgid "pe …tatiyampi kho sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa mātāpitaro sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and a third time,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:13.3"
msgid "“tvaṃ khosi, tāta sudinna, amhākaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparihato."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:13.4"
msgid "Na tvaṃ, tāta sudinna, kiñci dukkhassa jānāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:13.5"
msgid "Maraṇenapi mayaṃ te akāmakā vinā bhavissāma, kiṃ pana mayaṃ taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:13.6"
msgid "Uṭṭhehi, tāta sudinna, bhuñja ca piva ca paricārehi ca, bhuñjanto pivanto paricārento kāme paribhuñjanto puññāni karonto abhiramassu."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:13.7"
msgid "Na taṃ mayaṃ anujānāma agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:13.8"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho sudinno kalandaputto tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr "but Sudinna remained silent."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.3" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.3"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.49" href="#ms.49"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.1"
msgid "Atha kho sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa sahāyakā yena sudinno kalandaputto tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "Then Sudinnaʼs friends approached him"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and repeated three times what his parents had said."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.3"
msgid "“tvaṃ khosi, samma sudinna, mātāpitūnaṃ ekaputtako piyo manāpo sukhedhito sukhaparihato."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.4"
msgid "Na tvaṃ, samma sudinna, kiñci dukkhassa jānāsi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.5"
msgid "Maraṇenapi te mātāpitaro akāmakā vinā bhavissanti, kiṃ pana taṃ jīvantaṃ anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajāya."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.6"
msgid "Uṭṭhehi, samma sudinna, bhuñja ca piva ca paricārehi ca, bhuñjanto pivanto paricārento kāme paribhuñjanto puññāni karonto abhiramassu, na taṃ mātāpitaro anujānissanti agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.7"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sudinno kalandaputto tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.8"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.9"
msgid "tatiyampi kho sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa sahāyakā sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.10"
msgid "“tvaṃ khosi, samma sudinna … pe …"
msgstr ""

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.14" href="#Vin.3.14"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.25" href="#bd.1.25"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:14.11"
msgid "tatiyampi kho sudinno kalandaputto tuṇhī ahosi."
msgstr "But Sudinna made no response."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.4" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.4"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.50" href="#ms.50"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.1"
msgid "Atha kho sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa sahāyakā yena sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa mātāpitaro tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu;"
msgstr "Sudinna’s friends approached his parents"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa mātāpitaro etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.3"
msgid "“ammatātā, eso sudinno anantarahitāya bhūmiyā nipanno—‘idheva me maraṇaṃ bhavissati pabbajjā vā’ti."
msgstr "“Sudinna says heʼll either die right there on the bare ground or go forth."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.4"
msgid "Sace tumhe sudinnaṃ nānujānissatha agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya, tattheva maraṇaṃ āgamissati."
msgstr "If you donʼt allow him to go forth, heʼll die there."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.5"
msgid "Sace pana tumhe sudinnaṃ anujānissatha agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya, pabbajitampi naṃ dakkhissatha."
msgstr "But if you allow him to go forth, youʼll see him again afterwards."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.6"
msgid "Sace sudinno nābhiramissati agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya, kā tassa aññā gati bhavissati, idheva paccāgamissati."
msgstr "And if he doesnʼt enjoy the going forth, what alternative will he have but to come back here?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.7"
msgid "Anujānātha sudinnaṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr "So allow him to go forth.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.8"
msgid "“Anujānāma, tātā, sudinnaṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr "“We allow him,” they said."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.9"
msgid "Atha kho sudinnassa kalan­da­puttassa sahāyakā yena sudinno kalandaputto tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā sudinnaṃ kalandaputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "And Sudinna’s friends said to him,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:15.10"
msgid "“uṭṭhehi, samma sudinna, anuññātosi mātāpitūhi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti."
msgstr "“Get up, Sudinna, your parents have given you permission to go forth from home into homelessness.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.51" href="#ms.51"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.1"
msgid "Atha kho sudinno kalandaputto—"
msgstr "Sudinna thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.2"
msgid "“anuññātomhi kira mātāpitūhi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti,"
msgstr "“They say that my parents have given me permission to go forth,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.3"
msgid "haṭṭho udaggo pāṇinā gattāni paripuñchanto vuṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "and he got up, excited and joyful, stroking his limbs with his hands."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.4"
msgid "Atha kho sudinno kalandaputto katipāhaṃ balaṃ gāhetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "After spending a few days to regain his strength, he went to the Master,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.5"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr " bowed down to him, and sat down to one side."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.6"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sudinno kalandaputto bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He then said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.7"
msgid "“anuññāto ahaṃ, bhante, mātāpitūhi agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāya."
msgstr "“Venerable Sir, Iʼve got my parentsʼ permission to go forth from home into homelessness."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.8"
msgid "Pabbājetu maṃ bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "Please give me the going forth.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.15" href="#Vin.3.15"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.26" href="#bd.1.26"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.9"
msgid "Alattha kho sudinno kalandaputto bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ."
msgstr "He then received the going forth in the presence of the Master, and he received the full ordination."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.10"
msgid "Acirū­pasam­panno ca panāyasmā sudinno evarūpe dhutaguṇe samādāya vattati,"
msgstr "Not long afterwards he practiced these kinds of ascetic practices:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.11"
msgid "āraññiko hoti piṇḍapātiko paṃsukūliko sapadānacāriko,"
msgstr "living in the wilderness, going on almsround, wearing rag-robes, going on continuous almsround."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:16.12"
msgid "aññataraṃ vajjigāmaṃ upanissāya viharati."
msgstr "And he lived supported by a certain Vajjian village."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.5" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.5"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.52" href="#ms.52"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:17.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena vajjī dubbhikkhā hoti dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā, na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr "At that time the Vajjians were short of food and afflicted with hunger, with crops blighted and turned to straw, and it was not easy to get by almsfood."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:17.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa etadahosi—"
msgstr "Venerable Sudinna considered this and thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:17.3"
msgid "“etarahi kho vajjī dubbhikkhā dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā, na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:17.4"
msgid "Bahū kho pana me vesāliyaṃ ñātī aḍḍhā mahaddhanā mahābhogā pahūta­jāta­rūpa­rajatā pahūta­vit­tūpaka­raṇā pahūta­dhana­dhaññā."
msgstr "“I have many relatives in Vesālī who are rich."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:17.5"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ ñātī upanissāya vihareyyaṃ."
msgstr "Why don’t I live supported by them?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:17.6"
msgid "Ñātī maṃ nissāya dānāni dassanti puññāni karissanti, bhikkhū ca lābhaṃ lacchanti, ahañca piṇḍakena na kilamissāmī”ti."
msgstr "Because of me my relatives will be able to make offerings and make merit, the monks will obtain requisites, and I’ll have plenty of almsfood.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.53" href="#ms.53"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:18.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sudinno senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā patta­cīvara­mādāya yena vesālī tena pakkāmi."
msgstr "He then put his lodging in order, took his bowl and robe, and set out for Vesālī."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:18.2"
msgid "Anupubbena yena vesālī tadavasari."
msgstr "When he eventually arrived,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:18.3"
msgid "Tatra sudaṃ āyasmā sudinno vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭā­gāra­sālāyaṃ."
msgstr "he stayed in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.27" href="#bd.1.27"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:18.4"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho āyasmato sudinnassa ñātakā—"
msgstr "His relatives heard"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:18.5"
msgid "“sudinno kira kalandaputto vesāliṃ anuppatto”ti."
msgstr "that he had arrived in Vesālī,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:18.6"
msgid "Te āyasmato sudinnassa saṭṭhimatte thālipāke bhattābhihāraṃ abhihariṃsu."
msgstr "and they brought him sixty offerings of barley."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:18.7"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sudinno te saṭṭhimatte thālipāke bhikkhūnaṃ vissajjetvā pubbaṇ­ha­samayaṃ nivāsetvā patta­cīvara­mādāya kalandagāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr "Sudinna gave the offerings of barley to the monks, and taking his bowl and robe, he entered the village of Kalandaka for almsfood."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:18.8"
msgid "Kalandagāme sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno yena sakapitu nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr "As he was going on continuous almsround, he came to his own father’s house."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.6" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.6"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.54" href="#ms.54"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:19.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato sudinnassa ñātidāsī ābhidosikaṃ kummāsaṃ chaḍḍetukāmā hoti."
msgstr "Just then a female slave of Venerable Sudinna’s relatives wanted to throw away the previous evening’s porridge."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:19.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sudinno taṃ ñātidāsiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Sudinna said to her,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:19.3"
msgid "“sace taṃ, bhagini, ­chaḍḍa­nīya­dhammaṃ, idha me patte ākirā”ti."
msgstr "“If that’s to be thrown away, sister, put it here in my bowl.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:19.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa ñātidāsī taṃ ābhidosikaṃ kummāsaṃ āyasmato sudinnassa patte ākirantī hatthānañca pādānañca sarassa ca nimittaṃ aggahesi."
msgstr "As she was putting the porridge into his bowl, she recognized his hands, feet, and voice."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:19.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa ñātidāsī yenāyasmato sudinnassa mātā tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "She then went to his mother"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:19.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmato sudinnassa mātaraṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:19.7"
msgid "“yaggheyye, jāneyyāsi, ayyaputto sudinno anuppatto”ti."
msgstr "“Please know, madam, that the young master Sudinna is back.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:19.8"
msgid "“Sace, je, tvaṃ saccaṃ bhaṇasi, adāsiṃ taṃ karomī”ti."
msgstr "“If you speak the truth, Iʼll make you a free woman!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.55" href="#ms.55"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sudinno taṃ ābhidosikaṃ kummāsaṃ aññataraṃ kuṭṭamūlaṃ nissāya paribhuñjati."
msgstr "As Sudinna was eating the previous evening’s porridge at the base of a certain wall,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.16" href="#Vin.3.16"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.2"
msgid "Pitāpi kho āyasmato sudinnassa kammantā āgacchanto addasa āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ taṃ ābhidosikaṃ kummāsaṃ aññataraṃ kuṭṭamūlaṃ nissāya paribhuñjantaṃ."
msgstr "his father saw him as he was coming home from work."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.28" href="#bd.1.28"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.3"
msgid "Disvāna yenāyasmā sudinno tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "He approached him"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.5"
msgid "“atthi nāma, tāta sudinna, ābhidosikaṃ kummāsaṃ pari­bhuñjis­sasi."
msgstr "“But, Sudinna, isn’t there … and youʼre eating old porridge!"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.6"
msgid "Nanu nāma, tāta sudinna, sakaṃ gehaṃ gantabban”ti?"
msgstr "Isn’t there your own home to go to?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.7"
msgid "“Agamimha kho te, gahapati, gehaṃ."
msgstr "“We went to your house, householder."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.8"
msgid "Tatāyaṃ ābhidosiko kummāso”ti."
msgstr "That’s where we received this porridge.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.9"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa pitā āyasmato sudinnassa bāhāyaṃ gahetvā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Sudinna’s father took him by the arm and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.10"
msgid "“ehi, tāta sudinna, gharaṃ gamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“Come, let’s go to the house.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.11"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sudinno yena sakapitu nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Sudinna went to his father’s house"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.12"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "and sat down on a prepared seat."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.13"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa pitā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "His father said to him,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.14"
msgid "“bhuñja, tāta sudinnā”ti."
msgstr "“Eat, Sudinna.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.15"
msgid "“Alaṃ, gahapati,"
msgstr "“Thereʼs no need, householder;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.16"
msgid "kataṃ me ajja bhattakiccan”ti."
msgstr "Iʼve finished eating for today.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.17"
msgid "“Adhivāsehi, tāta sudinna, svātanāya bhattan”ti."
msgstr "“Then please come back for the meal tomorrow.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.18"
msgid "Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā sudinno tuṇhībhāvena."
msgstr "Sudinna consented by keeping silent,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:20.19"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sudinno uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr " and he rose from his seat and departed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.56" href="#ms.56"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:21.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa mātā tassā rattiyā accayena haritena gomayena pathaviṃ opuñjāpetvā"
msgstr "The following morning Sudinna’s mother had the ground smeared with fresh cow-dung,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:21.2"
msgid "dve puñje kārāpesi—ekaṃ hiraññassa, ekaṃ suvaṇṇassa."
msgstr "and she piled up two heaps, one with money and one with gold."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.29" href="#bd.1.29"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:21.3"
msgid "Tāva mahantā puñjā ahesuṃ, orato ṭhito puriso pārato ṭhitaṃ purisaṃ na passati; pārato ṭhito puriso orato ṭhitaṃ purisaṃ na passati."
msgstr "The heaps were so large that a man standing on one side could not see a man standing on the other."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:21.4"
msgid "Te puñje kilañjehi paṭic­chādā­petvā majjhe āsanaṃ paññāpetvā tirokaraṇīyaṃ parikkhipitvā āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇa­duti­yikaṃ āmantesi—"
msgstr "Hiding the heaps with screens and preparing a seat between them surrounded by a curtain, she said to Sudinna’s former wife,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.30" href="#bd.1.30"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:21.5"
msgid "“tena hi, vadhu, yena alaṅkārena alaṅkatā puttassa me sudinnassa piyā ahosi manāpā tena alaṅkārena alaṅkarā”ti."
msgstr "“Daughter-in-law, adorn yourself in the way our son Sudinna found you especially attractive."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:21.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, ayye”ti, kho āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇadutiyikā āyasmato sudinnassa mātuyā paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, madam.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.7" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.7"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.57" href="#ms.57"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sudinno pubbaṇ­ha­samayaṃ nivāsetvā patta­cīvara­mādāya yena sakapitu nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "That same morning, Venerable Sudinna dressed, took his bowl and robe, and went to his father’s house,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on the prepared seat."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.3"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa pitā yenāyasmā sudinno tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "His father approached him,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā te puñje vivarāpetvā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "uncovered the heaps, and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.5"
msgid "“idaṃ te, tāta sudinna, mātu mattikaṃ itthikāya itthidhanaṃ,"
msgstr "“This dowry, dear Sudinna, is the fortune from your mother, and itʼs yours."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.6"
msgid "aññaṃ pettikaṃ aññaṃ pitāmahaṃ."
msgstr "Another is the fortune from your father and another the fortune from your ancestors."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.7"
msgid "Labbhā, tāta sudinna, hīnāyāvattitvā bhogā ca bhuñjituṃ puññāni ca kātuṃ."
msgstr "Itʼs possible, Sudinna, to return to the lower life, enjoy wealth, and make merit."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.17" href="#Vin.3.17"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.8"
msgid "Ehi tvaṃ, tāta sudinna, hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjassu puññāni ca karohī”ti."
msgstr "Please do so.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.9"
msgid "“Tāta, na ussahāmi na visahāmi,"
msgstr "“I canʼt, father."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.10"
msgid "abhirato ahaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carāmī”ti."
msgstr "Iʼm enjoying the spiritual life.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.11"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr "Sudinna’s father repeated his request and Sudinna replied as before."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.12"
msgid "tatiyampi kho āyasmato sudinnassa pitā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Sudinna’s father then repeated his request a third time,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.13"
msgid "“idaṃ te, tāta sudinna, mātu mattikaṃ, itthikāya itthidhanaṃ, aññaṃ pettikaṃ, aññaṃ pitāmahaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.14"
msgid "Labbhā, tāta sudinna, hīnāyāvattitvā bhogā ca bhuñjituṃ puññāni ca kātuṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.15"
msgid "Ehi tvaṃ, tāta sudinna, hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjassu puññāni ca karohī”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.16"
msgid "“Vadeyyāma kho taṃ, gahapati, sace tvaṃ nātikaḍ­ḍhey­yāsī”ti."
msgstr "and Sudinna replied: “If you wouldnʼt get offended, householder, I could tell you what to do.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.17"
msgid "“Vadehi, tāta sudinnā”ti."
msgstr "“Speak, Sudinna.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.18"
msgid "“Tena hi tvaṃ, gahapati, mahante mahante sāṇipasibbake kārāpetvā"
msgstr "“Well then, householder, make some large bags of hemp-cloth,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.19"
msgid "hirañ­ña­suvaṇ­ṇassa pūrāpetvā"
msgstr "put all the money and gold inside,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.31" href="#bd.1.31"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.20"
msgid "sakaṭehi nibbāhāpetvā"
msgstr "take it all away in carts,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.21"
msgid "majjhe gaṅgāya sote opātehi."
msgstr "and dump it in the middle of the Ganges."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.22"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "And why?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.23"
msgid "Yañhi te, gahapati, bhavissati tatonidānaṃ bhayaṃ vā chambhitattaṃ vā lomahaṃso vā ārakkho vā so te na bhavissatī”ti."
msgstr "Because that way you would avoid the danger, fear, and terror that it will cause you, as well as the trouble with protection.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.24"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmato sudinnassa pitā anattamano ahosi—"
msgstr "His father became displeased and thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:22.25"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma putto sudinno evaṃ vakkhatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can our son Sudinna say such things?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.58" href="#ms.58"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:23.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa pitā āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇa­duti­yikaṃ āmantesi—"
msgstr "He then said to Sudinna’s former wife,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:23.2"
msgid "“tena hi, vadhu, tvaṃ piyā ca manāpā ca."
msgstr "“Well now, daughter-in-law, since you were dear to him,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:23.3"
msgid "Appeva nāma putto sudinno tuyhampi vacanaṃ kareyyā”ti."
msgstr "perhaps our son Sudinna will listen to you.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:23.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇadutiyikā āyasmato sudinnassa pādesu gahetvā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Venerable Sudinna’s former wife took hold of his feet and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:23.5"
msgid "“kīdisā nāma tā, ayyaputta, accharāyo yāsaṃ tvaṃ hetu brahmacariyaṃ carasī”ti?"
msgstr "“What are these nymphs like, young master, for which you lead the spiritual life?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:23.6"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, bhagini, accharānaṃ hetu brahmacariyaṃ carāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Sister, I donʼt lead the spiritual life for the sake of nymphs.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:23.7"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇadutiyikā—"
msgstr "His former wife thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:23.8"
msgid "“ajjatagge maṃ ayyaputto sudinno bhaginivādena samudācaratī”ti,"
msgstr "“From today the young master calls me ‘sister’,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:23.9"
msgid "“tattheva mucchitā papatā."
msgstr "and she fainted on the spot."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.8" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.8"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.59" href="#ms.59"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sudinno pitaraṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Sudinna said to his father,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.2"
msgid "“sace, gahapati, bhojanaṃ dātabbaṃ detha, mā no viheṭhayitthā”ti."
msgstr "“If thereʼs food to be given, householder, give it, but donʼt annoy me.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.3"
msgid "“Bhuñja, tāta sudinnā”ti."
msgstr "“Eat, Sudinna,” he said."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa mātā ca pitā ca āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesuṃ sampavāresuṃ."
msgstr "And with their own hands, Sudinna’s mother and father served and satisfied him with various kinds of fine food."

#. </p></div><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa mātā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ bhuttāviṃ onīta­patta­pāṇiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "When Sudinna had finished his meal, his mother said to him:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.6"
msgid "“idaṃ, tāta sudinna, kulaṃ aḍḍhaṃ mahaddhanaṃ mahābhogaṃ pahūta­jāta­rūpa­rajataṃ pahūta­vit­tūpaka­ra­ṇaṃ pahūta­dhana­dhaññaṃ."
msgstr "“Dear Sudinna, this family is rich."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.32" href="#bd.1.32"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.7"
msgid "Labbhā, tāta sudinna, hīnāyāvattitvā bhogā ca bhuñjituṃ puññāni ca kātuṃ."
msgstr "Itʼs possible to return to the lower life, enjoy wealth, and make merit."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.8"
msgid "Ehi tvaṃ, tāta sudinna, hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjassu puññāni ca karohī”ti."
msgstr "Please do so.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.9"
msgid "“Amma, na ussahāmi na visahāmi,"
msgstr "“Mother, I canʼt."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.18" href="#Vin.3.18"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:24.10"
msgid "abhirato ahaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carāmī”ti."
msgstr "Iʼm enjoying the spiritual life.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.60" href="#ms.60"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:25.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr "His mother repeated her request a second time, but got the same reply."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:25.2"
msgid "tatiyampi kho āyasmato sudinnassa mātā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "She then said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:25.3"
msgid "“idaṃ, tāta sudinna, kulaṃ aḍḍhaṃ mahaddhanaṃ mahābhogaṃ pahūta­jāta­rūpa­rajataṃ pahūta­vit­tūpaka­ra­ṇaṃ pahūta­dhana­dhaññaṃ."
msgstr "“This family, Sudinna, is rich."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:25.4"
msgid "Tena hi, tāta sudinna, bījakampi dehi—"
msgstr "Please give us a child;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:25.5"
msgid "mā no aputtakaṃ sāpateyyaṃ licchavayo atiharāpesun”ti."
msgstr "donʼt let the Licchavīs take over our heirless property.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:25.6"
msgid "“Etaṃ kho me, amma, sakkā kātun”ti."
msgstr "“Ok, mother, I can do that.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:25.7"
msgid "“Kahaṃ pana, tāta sudinna, etarahi viharasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Where are you staying at present?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:25.8"
msgid "“Mahāvane, ammā”ti."
msgstr "“In the Great Wood.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:25.9"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sudinno uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi."
msgstr "And he rose from his seat and departed."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.9" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.9"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.61" href="#ms.61"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa mātā āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇa­duti­yikaṃ āmantesi—"
msgstr "Sudinnaʼs mother said to his former wife,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.2"
msgid "“tena hi, vadhu, yadā utunī ahosi, pupphaṃ te uppannaṃ hoti, atha me āroceyyāsī”ti."
msgstr "“Daughter-in-law, as soon as you reach your fertile period, please tell me.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, ayye”ti kho āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇadutiyikā āyasmato sudinnassa mātuyā paccassosi."
msgstr "“Very well, madam,” she replied."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.4"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇadutiyikā nacirasseva utunī ahosi, pupphaṃsā uppajji."
msgstr "Not long afterwards Sudinna’s former wife reached her fertile period,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.5"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇadutiyikā āyasmato sudinnassa mātaraṃ etadavoca—“utunīmhi, ayye, pupphaṃ me uppannan”ti."
msgstr "and she reported it to Sudinna’s mother."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.6"
msgid "“Tena hi, vadhu, yena alaṅkārena alaṅkatā puttassa sudinnassa piyā ahosi manāpā tena alaṅkārena alaṅkarā”ti."
msgstr "“Daughter-in-law, adorn yourself in the way that our son Sudinna found you especially attractive.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ, ayye”ti kho āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇadutiyikā āyasmato sudinnassa mātuyā paccassosi."
msgstr "“Very well, madam,” she replied."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.33" href="#bd.1.33"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.8"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa mātā āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇa­duti­yikaṃ ādāya yena mahāvanaṃ yenāyasmā sudinno tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Then Sudinna’s mother, together with his former wife, approached Sudinna in the Great Wood,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and she said to him:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.10"
msgid "“idaṃ, tāta sudinna, kulaṃ aḍḍhaṃ mahaddhanaṃ mahābhogaṃ pahūta­jāta­rūpa­rajataṃ pahūta­vit­tūpaka­ra­ṇaṃ pahūta­dhana­dhaññaṃ."
msgstr "“This family, dear Sudinna, is rich."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.11"
msgid "Labbhā, tāta sudinna, hīnāyāvattitvā bhogā ca bhuñjituṃ puññāni ca kātuṃ."
msgstr "Itʼs possible to return to the lower life, enjoy wealth, and make merit."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.12"
msgid "Ehi tvaṃ, tāta sudinna, hīnāyāvattitvā bhoge ca bhuñjassu puññāni ca karohī”ti."
msgstr "Please do so.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.13"
msgid "“Amma, na ussahāmi na visahāmi,"
msgstr "“Mother, I canʼt."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:26.14"
msgid "abhirato ahaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carāmī”ti."
msgstr "Iʼm enjoying the spiritual life.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.62" href="#ms.62"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe …"
msgstr "His mother repeated her request a second time, but got the same reply."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.2"
msgid "tatiyampi kho āyasmato sudinnassa mātā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "She then said this:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.3"
msgid "“idaṃ, tāta sudinna, kulaṃ aḍḍhaṃ mahaddhanaṃ mahābhogaṃ pahūta­jāta­rūpa­rajataṃ pahūta­vit­tūpaka­ra­ṇaṃ pahūta­dhana­dhaññaṃ."
msgstr "“This family, Sudinna, is rich."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.4"
msgid "Tena hi, tāta sudinna, bījakampi dehi—"
msgstr "Please give us a child;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.5"
msgid "mā no aputtakaṃ sāpateyyaṃ licchavayo atiharāpesun”ti."
msgstr "donʼt let the Licchavīs take over our heirless property.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.6"
msgid "“Etaṃ kho me, amma, sakkā kātun”ti,"
msgstr "“Ok, mother, I can do that,” he said."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.7"
msgid "purāṇa­duti­yikāya bāhāyaṃ gahetvā"
msgstr "He then took his former wife by the arm,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.8"
msgid "mahāvanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā"
msgstr "plunged into the Great Wood and—"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.9"
msgid "apaññatte sikkhāpade anādīnavadasso"
msgstr "there being no training rule and he seeing no danger—"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.10"
msgid "purāṇa­duti­yikāya tikkhattuṃ methunaṃ dhammaṃ abhiviññāpesi."
msgstr "had sexual intercourse with her three times."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:27.11"
msgid "Sā tena gabbhaṃ gaṇhi."
msgstr "As a result she conceived."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.63" href="#ms.63"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.1"
msgid "Bhummā devā sad­da­manus­sā­vesuṃ—"
msgstr "The earth-gods cried out:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.2"
msgid "“nirabbudo vata bho bhikkhusaṃgho nirādīnavo;"
msgstr "“Good sirs, the Order of monks has been stainless and free from danger."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.3"
msgid "sudinnena kalandaputtena abbudaṃ uppāditaṃ, ādīnavo uppādito”ti."
msgstr "But Sudinna the Kalandaka has produced a stain, has produced danger.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.4"
msgid "Bhummānaṃ devānaṃ saddaṃ sutvā cātumahārājikā devā sad­da­manus­sā­vesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "The gods belonging to the heaven of the four great kings hearing the cry of the earth-gods in turn cried out …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.5"
msgid "tāvatiṃsā devā …"
msgstr "the Tāvatiṃsa gods …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.6"
msgid "yāmā devā …"
msgstr "the Yāma gods …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.7"
msgid "tusitā devā …"
msgstr "the Tusita gods …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.8"
msgid "nimmānaratī devā …"
msgstr "the gods who delight in creation …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.19" href="#Vin.3.19"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.9"
msgid "para­nimmita­vasavattī devā …"
msgstr "the gods who control the creation of others …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.10"
msgid "brahmakāyikā devā sad­da­manus­sā­vesuṃ—"
msgstr "the gods belonging to the retinue of the supreme beings in turn cried out:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.11"
msgid "“nirabbudo vata bho bhikkhusaṃgho nirādīnavo;"
msgstr "“Good sirs, the Order of monks has been stainless and free from danger."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.12"
msgid "sudinnena kalandaputtena abbudaṃ uppāditaṃ, ādīnavo uppādito”ti."
msgstr "But Sudinna the Kalandaka has produced a stain, has produced danger.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:28.13"
msgid "Itiha tena khaṇena tena muhuttena yāva brahmalokā saddo abbhuggacchi."
msgstr "Thus in that moment, in that instance, the news spread as far as the world of the supreme beings."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.64" href="#ms.64"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:29.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇadutiyikā tassa gabbhassa pari­pāka­man­vāya puttaṃ vijāyi."
msgstr "The pregnancy of Sudinna’s wife developed and she eventually gave birth to a son."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:29.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa sahāyakā tassa dārakassa bījakoti nāmaṃ akaṃsu."
msgstr "Sudinna’s friends called this boy Bījaka,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:29.3"
msgid "Āyasmato sudinnassa purāṇa­duti­yikāya bījakamātāti nāmaṃ akaṃsu."
msgstr "they called Sudinna’s former wife Bījaka’s mother,"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.34" href="#bd.1.34"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:29.4"
msgid "Āyasmato sudinnassa bījakapitāti nāmaṃ akaṃsu."
msgstr "and they called Venerable Sudinna Bījaka’s father."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:29.5"
msgid "Te aparena samayena ubho agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajitvā arahattaṃ sacchākaṃsu."
msgstr "After some time, they both went forth from home into homelessness, and they realized perfection."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.10" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.10"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.65" href="#ms.65"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:30.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa ahudeva kukkuccaṃ, ahu vippaṭisāro—"
msgstr "But Sudinna was anxious and remorseful, and he thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:30.2"
msgid "“alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ;"
msgstr "“This is truly bad for me,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:30.3"
msgid "yohaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitvā"
msgstr "that after going forth in such a well-proclaimed Teaching and training,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:30.4"
msgid "nāsakkhiṃ yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caritun”ti."
msgstr "I wasnʼt able to practice for life the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:30.5"
msgid "So teneva kukkuccena tena vippaṭisārena kiso ahosi lūkho dubbaṇṇo uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jāto dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gatto"
msgstr "And because of his anxiety and remorse, he became thin, haggard, and pale, his veins protruding all over his limbs;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:30.6"
msgid "antomano līnamano dukkhī dummano vippaṭisārī pajjhāyi."
msgstr "he became sad, sluggish, miserable, depressed, remorseful, weighed down by grief."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.66" href="#ms.66"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:31.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmato sudinnassa sahāyakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks who were Venerable Sudinna’s friends said to him:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:31.2"
msgid "“pubbe kho tvaṃ, āvuso sudinna, vaṇṇavā ahosi pīṇindriyo pasan­na­mukha­vaṇṇo vippa­sanna­chavi­vaṇṇo;"
msgstr "“Formerly, Sudinna, you were handsome, your features rounded, your face a good color, your skin clear."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:31.3"
msgid "so dāni tvaṃ etarahi kiso lūkho dubbaṇṇo uppaṇḍup­paṇḍuka­jāto dhama­ni­san­tha­ta­gatto antomano līnamano dukkhī dummano vippaṭisārī pajjhāyasi."
msgstr "But now youʼre thin, haggard, and pale, your veins protruding all over your limbs;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:31.4"
msgid "antomano līnamano dukkhī dummano vippaṭisārī pajjhāyasi."
msgstr "and youʼre sad, sluggish, miserable, depressed, remorseful, weighed down by grief."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:31.5"
msgid "Kacci no tvaṃ, āvuso sudinna, anabhirato brahmacariyaṃ carasī”ti?"
msgstr "Could it be that you lead the spiritual life dissatisfied?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.67" href="#ms.67"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:32.1"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, anabhirato brahmacariyaṃ carāmi."
msgstr "“I donʼt lead the spiritual life dissatisfied,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:32.2"
msgid "Atthi me pāpakammaṃ kataṃ;"
msgstr "but Iʼve done a bad deed."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:32.3"
msgid "purāṇa­duti­yikāya methuno dhammo paṭisevito;"
msgstr "Iʼve had sexual intercourse with my former wife."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:32.4"
msgid "tassa mayhaṃ, āvuso, ahudeva kukkuccaṃ ahu vippaṭisāro—"
msgstr "Thatʼs why Iʼm so miserable."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:32.5"
msgid "‘alābhā vata me, na vata me lābhā; dulladdhaṃ vata me, na vata me suladdhaṃ; yohaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitvā nāsakkhiṃ yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ caritun’”ti."
msgstr "I wasnʼt able to practice for life the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.68" href="#ms.68"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.1"
msgid "“Alañhi te, āvuso sudinna, kukkuccāya alaṃ vippaṭisārāya"
msgstr "“Sudinna, no wonder youʼre remorseful, no wonder you feel regret, "

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.2"
msgid "yaṃ tvaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitvā na sakkhissasi yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ."
msgstr "in that having gone forth in such a well-proclaimed Teaching and training you werenʼt able to practice for life the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.35" href="#bd.1.35"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.3"
msgid "Nanu, āvuso, bhagavatā aneka­pariyā­yena virāgāya dhammo desito, no sarāgāya;"
msgstr "Hasnʼt the Master taught in various ways for the sake of dispassion, not for the sake of passion;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.4"
msgid "visaṃyogāya dhammo desito, no saṃyogāya;"
msgstr "for the sake of freedom from bondage, not for the sake of bondage;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.5"
msgid "anupādānāya dhammo desito, no saupādānāya."
msgstr "for the sake of non-grasping, not for the sake of grasping?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.20" href="#Vin.3.20"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.6"
msgid "Tattha nāma tvaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā virāgāya dhamme desite sarāgāya cetessasi, visaṃyogāya dhamme desite saṃyogāya cetessasi, anupādānāya dhamme desite saupādānāya cetessasi."
msgstr "When the Master has taught in this way, how can you be intent upon passion, bondage, and grasping?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.7"
msgid "Nanu, āvuso, bhagavatā aneka­pariyā­yena rāgavirāgāya dhammo desito,"
msgstr "Hasnʼt the Master given many teachings for the  fading away of lust,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.8"
msgid "mada­nim­madanāya pipāsavinayāya ālaya­samug­ghātāya vaṭ­ṭupac­che­dāya taṇhākkhayāya virāgāya nirodhāya nibbānāya dhammo desito."
msgstr "for the clearing away of intoxication, for the removal of thirst, for the uprooting of attachment, for the cutting off of the round of birth and death, for the ending of craving, for fading away, for cessation, for extinguishment?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.9"
msgid "Nanu, āvuso, bhagavatā aneka­pariyā­yena kāmānaṃ pahānaṃ akkhātaṃ,"
msgstr "Hasnʼt the Master in various ways taught the abandoning of sense pleasures,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.10"
msgid "kāmasaññānaṃ pariññā akkhātā,"
msgstr "the full understanding of the perception of sense pleasures,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.11"
msgid "kāmapipāsānaṃ paṭivinayo akkhāto,"
msgstr "the abolishing of thirst for sense pleasures,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.12"
msgid "kāmavitakkānaṃ samugghāto akkhāto,"
msgstr "the elimination of thoughts of sense pleasures,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.13"
msgid "kāma­pari­ḷāhā­naṃ vūpasamo akkhāto."
msgstr "the stilling of the fever of sense pleasures?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, āvuso, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya, pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya."
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it or increase the confidence of those who have it,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:33.15"
msgid "Atha khvetaṃ, āvuso, appasan­nā­nañ­ceva appasādāya pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattāyā”ti."
msgstr "but it will hinder confidence in those without it, and it will cause some with confidence to change their minds.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="29"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.5.11" href="#Bu-Pj.1.5.11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.69" href="#ms.69"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:34.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "After criticizing Venerable Sudinna in various way, those monks informed the Master."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:34.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and questioned Venerable Sudinna:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.36" href="#bd.1.36"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:34.3"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, sudinna, purāṇa­duti­yikāya methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Sudinna, that you had sexual intercourse with your former wife?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:34.4"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“Itʼs true, Master.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="30"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.70" href="#ms.70"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.1"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.2"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appaṭirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“Foolish man, itʼs not suitable, itʼs not proper, itʼs not worthy of an ascetic, itʼs not allowable, itʼs not to be done."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.3"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitvā na sakkhissasi yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ."
msgstr "How could you go forth in such a well-proclaimed Teaching and training and not be able to practice for life the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.4"
msgid "Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, aneka­pariyā­yena virāgāya dhammo desito, no sarāgāya;"
msgstr "Havenʼt I given many teachings for the sake of dispassion, not for the sake of passion;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.5"
msgid "visaṃyogāya dhammo desito, no saṃyogāya;"
msgstr "for the sake of freedom from bondage, not for the sake of bondage;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.6"
msgid "anupādānāya dhammo desito, no saupādānāya."
msgstr "for the sake of non-grasping, not for the sake of grasping?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.7"
msgid "Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mayā virāgāya dhamme desite sarāgāya cetessasi, visaṃyogāya dhamme desite saṃyogāya cetessasi, anupādānāya dhamme desite saupādānāya cetessasi."
msgstr "When I have taught in this way, how can you be intent upon passion, bondage, and grasping?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.8"
msgid "Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, aneka­pariyā­yena rāgavirāgāya dhammo desito."
msgstr "Havenʼt I given many teachings for the fading away of lust,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.9"
msgid "Mada­nim­madanāya pipāsavinayāya ālaya­samug­ghātāya vaṭ­ṭupac­che­dāya taṇhākkhayāya virāgāya nirodhāya nibbānāya dhammo desito."
msgstr "for the clearing away of intoxication, for the removal of thirst, for the uprooting of attachment, for the cutting off of the round of birth and death, for the ending of craving, for fading away, for cessation, for extinguishment?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.10"
msgid "Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, aneka­pariyā­yena kāmānaṃ pahānaṃ akkhātaṃ,"
msgstr "Havenʼt I in various ways taught the abandoning of sense pleasures,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.11"
msgid "kāmasaññānaṃ pariññā akkhātā,"
msgstr "the full understanding of the perception of sense pleasures,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.12"
msgid "kāmapipāsānaṃ paṭivinayo akkhāto,"
msgstr "the abolishing of thirst for sense pleasures,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.13"
msgid "kāmavitakkānaṃ samugghāto akkhāto,"
msgstr "the elimination of thoughts of sense pleasures,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.14"
msgid "kāma­pari­ḷāhā­naṃ vūpasamo akkhāto."
msgstr "the stilling of the fever of sense pleasures?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.15"
msgid "Varaṃ te, moghapurisa, āsivisassa ghoravisassa mukhe aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ, na tveva mātugāmassa aṅgajāte aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ."
msgstr "It would be better, foolish man, for your penis to enter the mouth of a terrible and poisonous snake than to enter a woman."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.16"
msgid "Varaṃ te, moghapurisa, kaṇhasappassa mukhe aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ, na tveva mātugāmassa aṅgajāte aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ."
msgstr "It would be better for your penis to enter the mouth of a black snake than to enter a woman."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.17"
msgid "Varaṃ te, moghapurisa, aṅgārakāsuyā ādittāya sampajjalitāya sajotibhūtāya aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ, na tveva mātugāmassa aṅgajāte aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ."
msgstr "It would be better for your penis to enter a blazing charcoal pit than to enter a woman."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.18"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Whyʼs that?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.19"
msgid "Tatonidānañhi, moghapurisa, maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ, na tveva tappaccayā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya."
msgstr "Because for that reason, you might die or experience death-like suffering, but you wouldnʼt because of that be reborn in a bad destination."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.20"
msgid "Itonidānañca kho, moghapurisa, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya."
msgstr "But for <em>this</em> reason you might."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.21"
msgid "Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, yaṃ tvaṃ asaddhammaṃ gāmadhammaṃ vasaladhammaṃ duṭṭhullaṃ odakantikaṃ rahassaṃ dvayaṃ­dvaya­samā­pattiṃ samāpajjissasi,"
msgstr "Foolish man, youʼve practiced what is contrary to the true Teaching, the common practice, the low practice, the coarse practice, that which ends with a wash, that which is done in private, that which is done wherever there are couples."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.21" href="#Vin.3.21"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.37" href="#bd.1.37"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.22"
msgid " bahūnaṃ kho tvaṃ, moghapurisa, akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ ādikattā pubbaṅgamo."
msgstr "Youʼre the forerunner, the first performer of many unwholesome things."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.23"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya, pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya;"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it or increase the confidence of those who have it, "

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:35.24"
msgid "atha khvetaṃ, moghapurisa, appasan­nā­nañ­ceva appasādāya, pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattāyā”ti."
msgstr "but it will hinder confidence in those without it, and it will cause some with confidence to change their minds.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="31"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.71" href="#ms.71"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:36.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ sudinnaṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya dupposatāya mahicchatāya asantuṭṭhitāya saṅgaṇikāya kosajjassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitvā"
msgstr "Then the Master spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support and maintain, in dispraise of great desires, lack of contentment, socializing, and laziness;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:36.2"
msgid "aneka­pariyā­yena subharatāya suposatāya appicchassa santuṭṭhassa sallekhassa dhutassa pāsādikassa apacayassa vīriyā­rambhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitvā"
msgstr "but he spoke in praise in various ways of being easy to support and maintain, of desiring little, contentment, self-effacement, ascetic practices, serenity, decrease of defilements, and of the putting forth of energy."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:36.3"
msgid "bhikkhūnaṃ tadanuc­chavi­kaṃ tadanulomikaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "After giving a teaching on what is right and proper, he addressed the monks:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:36.4"
msgid "“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca—"
msgstr "“Because of this, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the monks for the following ten reasons:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.38" href="#bd.1.38"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:36.5"
msgid "saṃgha­suṭṭhu­tāya, saṃ­ghaphāsu­tāya, dummaṅkūnaṃ puggalānaṃ niggahāya, pesalānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ phāsuvihārāya, diṭṭha­dham­mikā­naṃ āsavānaṃ saṃvarāya, samparāyikānaṃ āsavānaṃ paṭighātāya, appasannānaṃ pasādāya, pasannānaṃ bhiyyobhāvāya, sad­dhammaṭ­ṭhitiyā, vina­yā­nugga­hāya."
msgstr "for the well-being of the Order, for the comfort of the Order, for the restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the restraint of corruptions in the present life, for avoiding corruptions in future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it, for the continuation of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:36.6"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:37.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "First preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="32"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.72" href="#ms.72"></a> 
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:37.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭiseveyya, pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk has sexual intercourse, he is expelled and not in communion.ʼ”"

#. </strong> 
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="33"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.73" href="#ms.73"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:38.1"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="34"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.74" href="#ms.74"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:39.1"
msgid "Sudinna­bhā­ṇavāro niṭṭhito."
msgstr "The section for recitation on Sudinna is finished."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:40.1"
msgid "2. Makkaṭīvatthu"
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="35"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.6" href="#Bu-Pj.1.6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.75" href="#ms.75"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu vesāliyaṃ mahāvane makkaṭiṃ āmisena upalāpetvā tassā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati."
msgstr "Some time later in the Great Wood near Vesālī, a certain monk befriended a female monkey by giving her food and then had sexual intercourse with her."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.2"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu pubbaṇ­ha­samayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaraṃ ādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr "One morning, he dressed, took his bowl and robe, and entered Vesālī for alms."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū senāsa­na­cārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā yena tassa bhikkhuno vihāro tenu­pasaṅka­miṃsu."
msgstr "Just then a number of monks who were inspecting the lodgings came to this monk’s dwelling."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.4"
msgid "Addasa kho sā makkaṭī te bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante."
msgstr "The female monkey saw the monks coming."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.5"
msgid "Disvāna yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "She went up to them,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ purato kaṭimpi cālesi cheppampi cālesi, kaṭimpi oḍḍi, nimittampi akāsi."
msgstr "shook her buttocks in front of them, wagged her tail, presented her buttocks, and made a gesture."

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.22" href="#Vin.3.22"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.39" href="#bd.1.39"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.7"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr "The monks thought,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.8"
msgid "“nissaṃsayaṃ kho so bhikkhu imissā makkaṭiyā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevatī”ti."
msgstr "“This monk must be having sexual intercourse with this monkey,”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.9"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nilīyiṃsu."
msgstr "and they hid to one side."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:41.10"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu vesāliyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya paṭikkami."
msgstr "Then, when that monk had finished his almsround in Vesālī and had returned with his almsfood,"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="36"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:42.1"
msgid "Atha kho sā makkaṭī yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.77" href="#ms.77"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:42.2"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ ekadesaṃ bhuñjitvā ekadesaṃ tassā makkaṭiyā adāsi."
msgstr "he ate one part himself and gave the rest to the female monkey."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:42.3"
msgid "Atha kho sā makkaṭī taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjitvā tassa bhikkhuno kaṭiṃ oḍḍi."
msgstr "After eating the food, the monkey presented her buttocks to the monk,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:42.4"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu tassā makkaṭiyā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati."
msgstr "and he had sexual intercourse with her."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="37"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "Those monks said to that monk,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.2"
msgid "“nanu, āvuso, bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ;"
msgstr "“Hasn’t a training rule been laid down by the Master?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.3"
msgid "kissa tvaṃ, āvuso, makkaṭiyā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevasī”ti?"
msgstr "Why then do you have sexual intercourse with a monkey?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.4"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ;"
msgstr "“Itʼs true that a training rule has been laid down by the Master,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.5"
msgid "tañca kho manussitthiyā, no tiracchā­na­gatāyā”ti."
msgstr "but it refers to human women, not to animals.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.6"
msgid "“Nanu, āvuso, tatheva taṃ hoti."
msgstr "“But thatʼs just the same."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.7"
msgid "Ananucchavikaṃ, āvuso, ananulomikaṃ appaṭirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "Itʼs not suitable, itʼs not proper, itʼs not worthy of an ascetic, itʼs not allowable, itʼs not to be done."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.8"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitvā na sakkhissasi yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ."
msgstr "How could you go forth in this well-proclaimed Teaching and training and not be able to practice for life the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.9"
msgid "Nanu, āvuso, bhagavatā aneka­pariyā­yena virāgāya dhammo desito, no sarāgāya … pe …"
msgstr "Hasnʼt the Master taught in various ways for the sake of dispassion …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.10"
msgid "kāma­pari­ḷāhā­naṃ vūpasamo akkhāto."
msgstr "the stilling of the fever of sense pleasures?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.11"
msgid "Netaṃ, āvuso, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya."
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it or increase the confidence of those who have it,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.12"
msgid "Atha khvetaṃ, āvuso, appasan­nā­nañ­ceva appasādāya, pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattāyā”ti."
msgstr "but it will hinder confidence in those without it, and it will cause some with confidence to change their minds.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:43.13"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "After criticizing that monk in various ways, they informed the Master."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="38"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.78" href="#ms.78"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ sannipātāpetvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master then had the Order of monks assembled and questioned that monk:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, makkaṭiyā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monk, that you had sexual intercourse with a monkey?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.3"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“Itʼs true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.4"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.5"
msgid "“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "“Foolish man, itʼs not suitable, itʼs not proper, itʼs not worthy of an ascetic, itʼs not allowable, itʼs not to be done."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.6"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitvā na sakkhissasi yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ."
msgstr "How could you go forth in such a well-proclaimed Teaching and training and not be able to practice for life the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.7"
msgid "Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, aneka­pariyā­yena virāgāya dhammo desito, no sarāgāya … pe …"
msgstr "Havenʼt I given many teachings for the sake of dispassion …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.8"
msgid "kāma­pari­ḷāhā­naṃ vūpasamo akkhāto."
msgstr "the stilling of the fever of sense pleasures?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.9"
msgid "Varaṃ te, moghapurisa, āsivisassa ghoravisassa mukhe aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ, na tveva makkaṭiyā aṅgajāte aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ."
msgstr "It would be better, foolish man, for your penis to enter the mouth of a terrible and poisonous snake than to enter a woman."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.10"
msgid "Varaṃ te, moghapurisa, kaṇhasappassa mukhe aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ, na tveva makkaṭiyā aṅgajāte aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ."
msgstr "It would be better for your penis to enter the mouth of a black snake than to enter a woman."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.11"
msgid "Varaṃ te, moghapurisa, aṅgārakāsuyā ādittāya sampajjalitāya sajotibhūtāya aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ, na tveva makkaṭiyā aṅgajāte aṅgajātaṃ pakkhittaṃ."
msgstr "It would be better for your penis to enter a blazing charcoal pit than to enter a woman."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.12"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Whyʼs that?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.13"
msgid "Tatonidānañhi, moghapurisa, maraṇaṃ vā nigaccheyya maraṇamattaṃ vā dukkhaṃ;"
msgstr "Because for that reason you might die or experience death-like suffering,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.14"
msgid "na tveva tappaccayā kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya."
msgstr "but you wouldnʼt because of that be reborn in a bad destination."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.15"
msgid "Itonidānañca kho, moghapurisa, kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya."
msgstr "But for <em>this</em> reason you might."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.16"
msgid "Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, yaṃ tvaṃ asaddhammaṃ gāmadhammaṃ vasaladhammaṃ duṭṭhullaṃ odakantikaṃ rahassaṃ dvayaṃ­dvaya­samā­pattiṃ samāpajjissasi."
msgstr "Foolish man, youʼve practiced what is contrary to the true Teaching, the common practice, the low practice, the coarse practice, that which ends with a wash, that which is done in private, that which is done wherever there are couples."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.40" href="#bd.1.40"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.17"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "Foolish man, this will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:44.18"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:45.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="39"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.79" href="#ms.79"></a> 
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:45.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭiseveyya antamaso tiracchā­na­gatā­yapi, pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk has sexual intercourse, even with a female animal, he is expelled and not in communion.ʼ”"

#. </strong> 
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="40"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.80" href="#ms.80"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:46.1"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="41"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.81" href="#ms.81"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:47.1"
msgid "Makkaṭīvatthu niṭṭhitaṃ."
msgstr "The story of the female monkey is finished."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:48.1"
msgid "3. San­tha­ta­bhā­ṇavāra"
msgstr "Third sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="42"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.7.1" href="#Bu-Pj.1.7"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.23" href="#Vin.3.23"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.82" href="#ms.82"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā vesālikā vajjiputtakā bhikkhū yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjiṃsu, yāvadatthaṃ supiṃsu, yāvadatthaṃ nhāyiṃsu."
msgstr "Around the same time, a number of Vajjian monks from Vesālī ate, slept, and bathed as much as they liked."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.2"
msgid "Yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjitvā yāvadatthaṃ supitvā yāvadatthaṃ nhāyitvā ayoniso manasi karitvā sikkhaṃ apaccakkhāya dubbalyaṃ anāvikatvā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭiseviṃsu."
msgstr "Doing so, and not reflecting properly, they had sexual intercourse, but without first renouncing the training and revealing their weakness."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.3"
msgid "Te aparena samayena ñātib­yasa­nenapi phuṭṭhā bhogab­yasa­nenapi phuṭṭhā rogab­yasa­nenapi phuṭṭhā"
msgstr "After some time, they were affected by loss of relatives, loss of property, and illness."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.4"
msgid "āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "They then approached Venerable Ānanda and said:"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.5"
msgid "“na mayaṃ, bhante ānanda, buddhagarahino na dhammagarahino na saṃghagarahino;"
msgstr "“Venerable Ānanda, we donʼt blame the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Order of monks;"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.41" href="#bd.1.41"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.6"
msgid "attagarahino mayaṃ, bhante ānanda, anaññagarahino."
msgstr "we only blame ourselves."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.7"
msgid "Mayamevamhā alakkhikā mayaṃ appapuññā,"
msgstr "We were unfortunate and had little merit:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.8"
msgid "ye mayaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitvā nāsakkhimhā yāvajīvaṃ paripuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ carituṃ."
msgstr "after going forth in such a well-proclaimed Teaching and training, we were unable to practice for life the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.9"
msgid "Idāni cepi mayaṃ, bhante ānanda, labheyyāma bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ labheyyāma upasampadaṃ, idānipi mayaṃ vipassakā kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pubba­rattā­pa­ra­rattaṃ bodhi­pak­khi­kā­naṃ dhammānaṃ bhāva­nā­nuyoga­manu­yuttā vihareyyāma."
msgstr "If we were now to obtain the going forth and the full ordination in the presence of the Master, we would have clarity about wholesome qualities and would be devoted day after day to developing the aids to awakening."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.10"
msgid "Sādhu, bhante ānanda, bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocehī”ti."
msgstr "Venerable Ānanda, please inform the Master of this matter.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.11"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho āyasmā ānando vesālikānaṃ vajji­putta­kā­naṃ paṭissuṇitvā"
msgstr "“Yes,” he replied."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:49.12"
msgid "yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "And he went to the Master and informed him."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="43"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.83" href="#ms.83"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:50.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhānametaṃ, ānanda, anavakāso yaṃ tathāgato vajjīnaṃ vā vajji­putta­kā­naṃ vā kāraṇā sāvakānaṃ pārājikaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ samūhaneyyā”ti."
msgstr "“Itʼs impossible, Ānanda, that the Buddha should abolish a training rule that entails expulsion because of the Vajjians.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="44"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.84" href="#ms.84"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:51.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "The Master then gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:51.2"
msgid "“yo, bhikkhave, sikkhaṃ apaccakkhāya dubbalyaṃ anāvikatvā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati so āgato na upasam­pā­detabbo."
msgstr "“Monks, if a monk, without first renouncing the training and revealing his weakness, has sexual intercourse, he may not receive the full ordination."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:51.3"
msgid "Yo ca kho, bhikkhave, sikkhaṃ paccakkhāya dubbalyaṃ āvikatvā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭisevati so āgato upasam­pā­detabbo."
msgstr "But, monks, if someone has sexual intercourse after first renouncing the training and revealing his weakness, he may receive the full ordination."

#. </strong>
#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:51.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:52.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="45"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.85" href="#ms.85"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.42" href="#bd.1.42"></a> 
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:52.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhā­sājīva­samā­panno sikkhaṃ apaccakkhāya dubbalyaṃ anāvikatvā methunaṃ dhammaṃ paṭiseveyya, antamaso tiracchā­na­gatā­yapi, pārājiko hoti asaṃvāso”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk, after taking on the monks’ training and way of life, without first renouncing the training and revealing his weakness, has sexual intercourse, even with a female animal, he is expelled and not in communion.ʼ”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:52.3"
msgid "(<em>1</em>:<strong>1</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:52.4"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="Bu-Pj.1.8"></a> <a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.8.1" href="#Bu-Pj.1.8.1"></a> <a class="ms-pa" id="ms.86" href="#ms.86"></a><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:52.5"
msgid "Yo panāti "
msgstr "A:"

#. </strong> 
#. <a class="sc" id="46"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.24" href="#Vin.3.24"></a> 
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:53.1"
msgid "yo yādiso yathāyutto yathājacco yathānāmo yathāgotto yathāsīlo yathāvihārī yathāgocaro thero vā navo vā majjhimo vā."
msgstr "whoever, of such a kind, of such activity, of such social standing, of such name, of such family, of such conduct, of such behavior, of such association, who is senior, who is junior, or who is of middle standing—"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:53.2"
msgid "Eso vuccati “yo panā”ti."
msgstr "this is called “a.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="47"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.87" href="#ms.87"></a> 
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.1"
msgid "Bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </strong> 
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.2"
msgid "bhikkhakoti bhikkhu,"
msgstr "he is a monk because he lives on alms;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.3"
msgid "bhikkhācariyaṃ ajjhupagatoti bhikkhu,"
msgstr "a monk because he has gone over to living on alms;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.4"
msgid "bhinna­paṭa­dha­roti bhikkhu, "
msgstr "a monk because he is one who wears a patchwork cloth;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.5"
msgid "samaññāya bhikkhu, "
msgstr "a monk by convention;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.6"
msgid "paṭiññāya bhikkhu, "
msgstr "a monk on account of his acknowledgment;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.7"
msgid "ehi bhikkhūti bhikkhu,"
msgstr "a “come, monk” monk;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.8"
msgid "tīhi saraṇagamanehi upasampannoti bhikkhu,"
msgstr "a monk given the full ordination by going to the three refuges;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.9"
msgid "bhadro bhikkhu,"
msgstr "a good monk;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.10"
msgid "sāro bhikkhu,"
msgstr "a monk of substance;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.11"
msgid "sekho bhikkhu,"
msgstr "a trainee monk;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.12"
msgid "asekho bhikkhu,"
msgstr "a fully trained monk;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.13"
msgid "samaggena saṃghena ñatti­catut­thena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena upasampannoti bhikkhu."
msgstr "a monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order of monks through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.14"
msgid "Tatra yvāyaṃ bhikkhu samaggena saṃghena ñatti­catut­thena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena upasampanno,"
msgstr "The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order of monks through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements, which is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:54.15"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="48"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.88" href="#ms.88"></a> 
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:55.1"
msgid "Sikkhāti tisso sikkhā—"
msgstr "Training:"

#. </strong> 
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:55.2"
msgid "tisso sikkhā—"
msgstr "the three trainings:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.43" href="#bd.1.43"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:55.3"
msgid "adhisīlasikkhā, adhi­citta­sikkhā, adhipañ­ñā­sikkhā."
msgstr "the training in the higher morality, the training in the higher mind, the training in the higher wisdom."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:55.4"
msgid "Tatra yāyaṃ adhisīlasikkhā, ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā sikkhāti."
msgstr "The training in the higher morality is the training meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="49"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.89" href="#ms.89"></a> 
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:56.1"
msgid "Sājīvaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Way of life:"

#. </strong> 
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:56.2"
msgid "yaṃ bhagavatā paññattaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ,"
msgstr "whatever training rule has been laid down by the Master—"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:56.3"
msgid "etaṃ sājīvaṃ nāma."
msgstr "this is called “way of life.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:56.4"
msgid "Tasmiṃ sikkhati, tena vuccati sājīva­samā­pan­noti."
msgstr "One trains in this; therefore it is called “after taking on […] the way of life.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="50"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="Bu-Pj.1.8.2" href="#Bu-Pj.1.8.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.90" href="#ms.90"></a> 
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:57.1"
msgid "Sikkhaṃ apaccakkhāya dubbalyaṃ anāvikatvāti"
msgstr "Without first renouncing the training and revealing his weakness:"

#. </strong> 
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:57.2"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, dubbal­yā­vi­kammañ­ceva hoti sikkhā ca apaccakkhātā;"
msgstr "“There is, monks, a revealing of weakness without the training being renounced;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:57.3"
msgid "atthi, bhikkhave, dubbal­yā­vi­kammañ­ceva hoti sikkhā ca paccakkhātā."
msgstr "and there is a revealing of weakness together with the training being renounced."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.91" href="#ms.91"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, dubbal­yā­vi­kammañ­ceva hoti sikkhā ca apaccakkhātā."
msgstr "And how is there a revealing of weakness without the training being renounced?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.2"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu ukkaṇṭhito anabhirato sāmaññā cavitukāmo"
msgstr "Here a monk is dissatisfied, discontent, desiring to give up the life of an ascetic;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.3"
msgid "bhikkhubhāvaṃ aṭṭīyamāno harāyamāno jigucchamāno"
msgstr "troubled, ashamed, and disgusted with monkhood;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.4"
msgid "gihibhāvaṃ patthayamāno"
msgstr "longing to be a householder,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.5"
msgid "upāsakabhāvaṃ patthayamāno"
msgstr "longing to be a lay follower,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.6"
msgid "ārāmikabhāvaṃ patthayamāno"
msgstr "longing to be a monastery attendant,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.7"
msgid "sāmaṇerabhāvaṃ patthayamāno"
msgstr "longing to be a novice,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.8"
msgid "titthiyabhāvaṃ patthayamāno"
msgstr "longing to be an ascetic of another sect,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.9"
msgid "titthi­ya­sāvaka­bhāvaṃ patthayamāno"
msgstr "longing to be a follower of another sect,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.10"
msgid "assamaṇabhāvaṃ patthayamāno"
msgstr "longing not to be an ascetic,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.11"
msgid "asakya­put­ti­ya­bhāvaṃ patthayamāno—"
msgstr "longing not to be a son of the Sakyan,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.12"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ buddhaṃ paccakkheyyan”ti vadati viññāpeti."
msgstr "and he says and declares: ‘Why don’t I renounce the Buddha?’"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:58.13"
msgid "Evampi, bhikkhave, dubbal­yā­vi­kammañ­ceva hoti sikkhā ca apaccakkhātā."
msgstr "In this way, monks, thereʼs a revealing of weakness without the training being renounced."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.92" href="#ms.92"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.1"
msgid "Atha vā pana ukkaṇṭhito anabhirato sāmaññā cavitukāmo"
msgstr "Or again, dissatisfied, discontent, desiring to give up the life of an ascetic;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.2"
msgid "bhikkhubhāvaṃ aṭṭīyamāno harāyamāno jigucchamāno"
msgstr "troubled, ashamed, and disgusted with monkhood;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.3"
msgid "gihibhāvaṃ patthayamāno … pe …"
msgstr "longing to be a householder …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.4"
msgid "asakya­put­ti­ya­bhāvaṃ patthayamāno—"
msgstr "longing not to be a son of the Sakyan,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.5"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ dhammaṃ paccakkheyyan”ti vadati viññāpeti … pe …"
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘Why don’t I renounce the Teaching?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.6"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ saṃghaṃ …"
msgstr "the Order?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.7"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ sikkhaṃ …"
msgstr "the practice?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.8"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ vinayaṃ …"
msgstr "the training?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.9"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ pātimokkhaṃ …"
msgstr "the monastic code?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.10"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ uddesaṃ …"
msgstr "the recital?’ …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.25" href="#Vin.3.25"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.11"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ upajjhāyaṃ …"
msgstr "my preceptor?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.12"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ ācariyaṃ …"
msgstr "my teacher?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.13"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ sad­dhi­vihā­ri­kaṃ …"
msgstr "being a student?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.14"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ antevāsikaṃ …"
msgstr "being a pupil?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.15"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ samā­nu­paj­jhā­ya­kaṃ …"
msgstr "our common preceptor?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.16"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ samā­nā­cari­ya­kaṃ …"
msgstr "our common teacher?’ …"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.44" href="#bd.1.44"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.17"
msgid "yannūnāhaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ paccakkheyyan”ti vadati viññāpeti."
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘Why don’t I renounce my fellow monks?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.18"
msgid "“Yannūnāhaṃ gihī assan”ti vadati viññāpeti."
msgstr "‘Why don’t I become a householder?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.19"
msgid "“Yannūnāhaṃ upāsako assan”ti …"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I become a lay follower?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.20"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ ārāmiko assan”ti …"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I become a monastery attendant?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.21"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ sāmaṇero assan”ti …"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I become a novice?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.22"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ titthiyo assan”ti …"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I become an ascetic of another sect?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.23"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ titthiyasāvako assan”ti …"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I become a follower of another sect?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.24"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ assamaṇo assan”ti …"
msgstr "‘Why don’t I become a non-ascetic?’ …"

#. <span class="note" hidden>I have added two sets of ellipses points that seem to be missing from the Pali of MS.1.92. The missing sets are between “he says and declares: ‘Why don’t I renounce my fellow monks?’” and “he says and declares: ‘Why don’t I become a householder?’” and between “he says and declares: ‘Why don’t I become a householder?’” and “‘Why don’t I become a lay follower?’”</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.25"
msgid "“yannūnāhaṃ asakyaputtiyo assan”ti vadati viññāpeti."
msgstr "‘Why don’t I become a non-son-of-the-Sakyan?’"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:59.26"
msgid "Evampi, bhikkhave, dubbal­yā­vi­kammañ­ceva hoti sikkhā ca apaccakkhātā."
msgstr "In this way too, monks, thereʼs a revealing of weakness without the training being renounced."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.93" href="#ms.93"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.1"
msgid "Atha vā pana ukkaṇṭhito anabhirato sāmaññā cavitukāmo"
msgstr "Or again, dissatisfied, discontent, desiring to give up the life of an ascetic;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.2"
msgid "bhikkhubhāvaṃ aṭṭīyamāno harāyamāno jigucchamāno"
msgstr "troubled, ashamed, and disgusted with monkhood;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.3"
msgid "gihibhāvaṃ patthayamāno … pe …"
msgstr "longing to be a householder …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.4"
msgid "asakya­put­ti­ya­bhāvaṃ patthayamāno—"
msgstr "longing not to be a son of the Sakyan,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.5"
msgid "“yadi panāhaṃ buddhaṃ paccakkheyyan”ti vadati viññāpeti … pe …"
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘But if I renounced the Buddha’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.6"
msgid "“yadi panāhaṃ asakyaputtiyo assan”ti vadati viññāpeti … pe …"
msgstr "he says and declares: But if I weren’t a son of the Sakyan’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.7"
msgid "“apāhaṃ buddhaṃ paccakkheyyan”ti vadati viññāpeti … pe …"
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘Perhaps I should renounce the Buddha?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.8"
msgid "“apāhaṃ asakyaputtiyo assan”ti vadati viññāpeti … pe …"
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘Perhaps I shouldn’t be a son of the Sakyan?’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.9"
msgid "“handāhaṃ buddhaṃ paccakkheyyan”ti vadati viññāpeti … pe …"
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘Well then, I should renounce the Buddha’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.10"
msgid "“handāhaṃ asakyaputtiyo assan”ti vadati viññāpeti … pe …"
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘Well then, I shouldn’t be a son of the Sakyan’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.11"
msgid "“hoti me buddhaṃ paccakkheyyan”ti vadati viññāpeti … pe …"
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘I think I should renounce the Buddha’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.12"
msgid "“hoti me asakyaputtiyo assan”ti vadati viññāpeti."
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘I think I shouldn’t be a son of the Sakyan.’"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:60.13"
msgid "Evampi, bhikkhave, dubbal­yā­vi­kammañ­ceva hoti sikkhā ca apaccakkhātā."
msgstr "In this way too, monks, thereʼs a revealing of weakness without the training being renounced."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms.94" href="#ms.94"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.1"
msgid "Atha vā pana ukkaṇṭhito anabhirato sāmaññā cavitukāmo"
msgstr "Or again, dissatisfied, discontent, desiring to give up the life of an ascetic;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.2"
msgid "bhikkhubhāvaṃ aṭṭīyamāno harāyamāno jigucchamāno"
msgstr "troubled, ashamed, and disgusted with monkhood;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.3"
msgid "gihibhāvaṃ patthayamāno … pe …"
msgstr "longing to be a householder …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.4"
msgid "asakya­put­ti­ya­bhāvaṃ patthayamāno"
msgstr "longing not to be a son of the Sakyan,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.5"
msgid "“mātaraṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "he says and declares: ‘I remember my mother’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.6"
msgid "“pitaraṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my father’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.7"
msgid "“bhātaraṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my brother’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.8"
msgid "“bhaginiṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my sister’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.9"
msgid "“puttaṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my son’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.10"
msgid "“dhītaraṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my daughter’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.11"
msgid "“pajāpatiṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my wife’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.12"
msgid "“ñātake sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my relations’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.13"
msgid "“mitte sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my friends’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.14"
msgid "“gāmaṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my village’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.15"
msgid "“nigamaṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my town’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.16"
msgid "“khettaṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my fields’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.17"
msgid "“vatthuṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my land’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.18"
msgid "“hiraññaṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my money’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.19"
msgid "“suvaṇṇaṃ sarāmī”ti vadati viññāpeti …"
msgstr "‘I remember my gold’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-pj1:61.20"
